18d3365f-c6d7-4d5e-85c1-0011fd125368.title: VIOLENT ACTS
18d3365f-c6d7-4d5e-85c1-0011fd125368.definition: Codes in this division apply to injuries that are the result of intentional violent acts by a person. Such injuries may be inflicted by another person or by oneself. The injury from violent acts may be physical or mental/emotional. The injured worker could be directly involved in the violent act, as either a target of violence or harmed due to gross negligence during commission of a crime. They may also be the indirect victim of violence such as a friendly fire strike during a violent shoot out or witnessing a violent act. Injuries resulting from an intent to harm are considered to be acts of violence regardless of the mental capacity or state of the aggressor. Injuries involving the normal worksite tasks and actions of co-workers should be considered accidental unless information to indicate harmful intent is provided.
18d3365f-c6d7-4d5e-85c1-0011fd125368.includes: Intentional violent acts by a person; inadvertent victims harmed during the commission of a violent crime; injuries to persons intervening in violent situations; injuries to bystanders or witnesses of violent acts;  injuries from falls or contact as  a result of avoiding a violent act by a person; intentional injuries by persons with diminished mental capacity even while being restrained, moved, or cared for by the worker; distress from witnessing a violent act or the aftermath of a violent act
18d3365f-c6d7-4d5e-85c1-0011fd125368.excludes: Unintentional or intent unknown injuries resulting from direct contact with a person (61); intentional physical contact without malicious intent during police, military, or martial arts training and during sporting events and training (611); hit by a ball thrown by another person without malicious intent (6429); accidental injuries from all types of guns (641); transportation incidents unless the intent was to injure the worker (Division 2); injuries resulting from contact with animals (62); unintentional or intent unknown drug overdoses (551); exposures to infectious agents (55)

2d352e39-ca06-43fe-afb7-a964fc11b52b.title: Violent acts— unspecified
2d352e39-ca06-43fe-afb7-a964fc11b52b.definition: Intentional violent acts when it is unknown whether the injury was self-inflicted or inflicted by another person regardless of whether the injured worker was the intended target or an inadvertent victim.
2d352e39-ca06-43fe-afb7-a964fc11b52b.includes: Gunshot wound when unknown if inflicted by self or other person
2d352e39-ca06-43fe-afb7-a964fc11b52b.excludes: Injuries from unintentional actions or actions of unknown intent (61)

dfe7fc8c-b5f6-4aa1-8f94-0f71cafa4326.title: Violent acts by other person
dfe7fc8c-b5f6-4aa1-8f94-0f71cafa4326.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of violent acts by persons other than the injured worker when it is known that the act was intentional. The injured worker could be the intended target or an inadvertent victim. The worker could be physically injured or experience stress from the intentional violent action of another person.
dfe7fc8c-b5f6-4aa1-8f94-0f71cafa4326.includes: Injuries or distress sustained while attempting to restrain a person acting violently or while breaking up a fight; stress from being present during a violent act by a person which could result in physical harm to the worker, even if no injury occurs
dfe7fc8c-b5f6-4aa1-8f94-0f71cafa4326.excludes: Accidental or unintentional  contact with another person (61); unintentional injuries resulting from intentional physical contact (e.g. contact sports injuries) (611); intentional, self inflicted injuries (120); distress from witnessing a violent act or the aftermath of a violent act that does not threaten the worker (13); contact with another without resistance, such as from an orderly arrest, detention, or take down (61)

76056c2a-071a-43a7-a489-0696737e1c54.title: Violent acts by other person— unspecified
76056c2a-071a-43a7-a489-0696737e1c54.definition: Intentionally violent acts by a person other than the injured worker when the specific type of action(s) specified in codes 111 to 119 are unknown is unknown.
76056c2a-071a-43a7-a489-0696737e1c54.includes: Nonspecific violent acts by a person on another described as any of the following:  altercation, attack, or assault; fighting with another person; injury due to violent acts by aggressive, agitated, or combative person; stress from being the victim or intended victim of an unknown  violent act

aa948b2b-61f9-413a-bfbd-f3f67d85427e.title: Shooting by other person
aa948b2b-61f9-413a-bfbd-f3f67d85427e.definition: Instances where a person is shot by another person in a violent situation, acting either with intent to harm others or with disregard for human life. Inadvertent shooting(s) in a violent situation when the victim was not the intended target are included here. Weapons may be firearms or air-powered gun shooting bullets or other projectiles.
aa948b2b-61f9-413a-bfbd-f3f67d85427e.excludes: gun intentionally fired in a violent situation when the injured worker was not the intended target

5c074c65-c1c2-44b6-bbda-7187dd81ab67.title: Stabbing, cutting, slashing by other person
5c074c65-c1c2-44b6-bbda-7187dd81ab67.definition: Instances where a person is stabbed, cut, slashed or pierced by another person in a violent situation, acting either with intent to harm others or in gross negligence of human life and safety, regardless of whether the victim was the intended target. Injuries may be inflicted by actual weapons or improvised objects.
5c074c65-c1c2-44b6-bbda-7187dd81ab67.includes: Stabbed, slashed, cut, lacerated, punctured by knife or sharp instrument; cases of use of a sharp instrument as a weapon by another person; stress due to attempted stabbing

ff7728de-4da1-459d-94bd-0aa90a344efa.title: Strangulation, asphyxiation by other person
ff7728de-4da1-459d-94bd-0aa90a344efa.definition: Choking, strangulation, smothering or any other type of mechanical asphyxiation by another person. Injuries may be inflicted with hands, weapons, or improvised objects.
ff7728de-4da1-459d-94bd-0aa90a344efa.includes: strangulation using rope, chain, or other ligature; asphyxiation using covering of mouth and nose with tape, pillow, etc.; intentional drowning; stress from attempted strangulation or asphyxiation even if no physical harm occurred
ff7728de-4da1-459d-94bd-0aa90a344efa.excludes: self-strangulation, asphyxiation or hanging (122); asphyxiation due to entrapment in objects or equipment (Division 6); asphyxiation due to exposure to harmful substances or environments (Division 5)

58f3582f-59c2-4fbc-ade5-8af48cadc329.title: Hitting, kicking, beating by other person
58f3582f-59c2-4fbc-ade5-8af48cadc329.definition: Violent physical contact with another person using her/his body or a handheld object, except when contact results in strangulation. This includes Injuries may be inflicted by the person's body, weapons, or improvised objects.
58f3582f-59c2-4fbc-ade5-8af48cadc329.includes: physical assault without mention of weapon; Intentional acts of punching, clubbing, bludgeoning, hitting with weapon, grabbing, grappling, biting, pushing, pinching, squeezing, shoving, butting, scratching, and twisting or bending appendages
58f3582f-59c2-4fbc-ade5-8af48cadc329.excludes: Strangulation (113); assault, stabbing with sharp objects, knife (112); injuries by animals (62); simulated fighting or horseplay (61); unintentional or intent unknown physical contact with another person such as being struck by a falling person (61); intentionally throwing an object at another person (119)

ee08e37a-8152-4487-8887-300861d5a811.title: Hitting, kicking, beating by other person— unspecified
ee08e37a-8152-4487-8887-300861d5a811.definition: Violent physical contact with another person using her/his body or a handheld object, when a more specific code from 1441-1449 cannot be determined.

1fdfbb9f-5765-45ba-8da8-ae4bd0ce1b3f.title: Hitting, kicking, beating by other person while providing protective services
1fdfbb9f-5765-45ba-8da8-ae4bd0ce1b3f.definition: Injury due to direct physical contact with another person while attempting to restrain or arrest suspects or inmates in a law enforcement, corrections, security, or peace-keeping capacity.
1fdfbb9f-5765-45ba-8da8-ae4bd0ce1b3f.includes: heart attack after physical struggle; prison, corrections work;

28d6a579-49c0-4295-b094-c353ccdbb388.title: Hitting, kicking, beating by other person while providing medical or custodial care
28d6a579-49c0-4295-b094-c353ccdbb388.definition: Injury due to direct physical contact with another person while restraining a patient, student, or other ward.
28d6a579-49c0-4295-b094-c353ccdbb388.includes: Biting by patient or person in care
28d6a579-49c0-4295-b094-c353ccdbb388.excludes: special needs or foster group home care

a5f9adc8-2b78-4fb4-aa5f-03e470b0d7cb.title: Hitting, kicking, beating by other person— n.e.c.
a5f9adc8-2b78-4fb4-aa5f-03e470b0d7cb.definition: All other instance of Injury due to direct physical contact except for during arrest or providing care.
a5f9adc8-2b78-4fb4-aa5f-03e470b0d7cb.includes: Hitting, kicking, beating injuries due to co-worker violence; robbers and other assailants; at-work domestic violence

cdaa3f63-92d7-4d4e-88b8-f8f89fff1f1f.title: Bombing, arson by other person
cdaa3f63-92d7-4d4e-88b8-f8f89fff1f1f.definition: Bombing or arson of a structure, vehicle or other object by a person with violent or destructive intent. Arson is defined as the criminal act of deliberately setting fire to property for the purpose of inflicting damage or harm or for financial gain.
cdaa3f63-92d7-4d4e-88b8-f8f89fff1f1f.includes: assault by arson or incendiary device; unintentional injuries as a result of intentional arson, such as a firefighter injuries from trying to extinguish an arson fire; stress due to being part of bombing or arson even if no physical harm occurred
cdaa3f63-92d7-4d4e-88b8-f8f89fff1f1f.excludes: Fire or explosions-- accidental or unknown cause (Division 3)

24e715f1-08bc-42d8-ace1-05e113cf48dd.title: Rape, sexual assault by other person
24e715f1-08bc-42d8-ace1-05e113cf48dd.definition: Physical sexual contact by a person carried out forcibly or under threat of injury and against another person's will.
24e715f1-08bc-42d8-ace1-05e113cf48dd.includes: Coerced sexual acts with or without physical force

41326859-11dc-46ca-98de-ce8692c6eb28.title: Threat, harassment by other person
41326859-11dc-46ca-98de-ce8692c6eb28.definition: Verbal or nonverbal communications of intention to inflict physical harm or cause nonphysical pain, injury, damage, or take some other hostile action on a person or that person's loved ones by another person. In order to select this code, there must have been a reasonable fear of violent action or a pattern intimidating behaviors (such as would amount to cause for a restraining order), such as stalking or harassment.
41326859-11dc-46ca-98de-ce8692c6eb28.includes: non-verbal communications of physical harm; online bullying, harassment; threats of rape; deliberate menacing body posture; brandishing or pointing  weapon; robberies without assault; coercion and blackmail; stalking; suggesting that a person kill or harm themselves; violation of restraining order
41326859-11dc-46ca-98de-ce8692c6eb28.excludes: Argument or intimidation without threats of harm (57);  "toxic work environment" (57); unintentional verbal intimidation (57); missed intended shooting target (111); unintentional intimidation (57); (code the violent act over the threat)

6d00ddad-e2fe-45a1-8d86-b71521d3428b.title: Multiple violent acts by other person
6d00ddad-e2fe-45a1-8d86-b71521d3428b.definition: Combination of two or more  different violent acts from codes 111 to 117 when it cannot be determined which act produced the more severe injury.

e7c4dd0b-891f-470f-b3b3-7128ee25902f.title: Intentional violence by other person— n.e.c.
e7c4dd0b-891f-470f-b3b3-7128ee25902f.definition: Violent acts by a person that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes from 111 to 118.
e7c4dd0b-891f-470f-b3b3-7128ee25902f.includes: Vehicular assault; hit by intentionally thrown object; intentional shooting by stun gun, BB gun, nail gun, or bow and arrow; human use of attack animal; being held against will, kidnapping without other injury;  intentional pepper-spraying; unwanted sexual displays or exposures; injuries from falls or contact as a result of avoiding a violent act by a person; spitting or throwing bodily excrements
e7c4dd0b-891f-470f-b3b3-7128ee25902f.excludes: Accidental or unintentional  contact with another person (61)

7e70addb-5d0a-4ff3-b2d0-67a71d0b1f04.title: Intentional self-harm
7e70addb-5d0a-4ff3-b2d0-67a71d0b1f04.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are intentional and self-inflicted. Injuries resulting from the normal worksite tasks and actions of the worker are generally considered accidental unless information to the contrary is provided indicating suicide or attempted suicide or other attempt to injure oneself on purpose.
7e70addb-5d0a-4ff3-b2d0-67a71d0b1f04.excludes: Accidental drug overdoses and overdoses where intent is undetermined (55)

a0ab0a55-d01f-4b46-b44c-5d604a50d7ba.title: Intentional self-harm— unspecified
a0ab0a55-d01f-4b46-b44c-5d604a50d7ba.definition: Self-inflicted injuries with intent to harm when the specific type of action specified in codes 211 to 129 is unknown.

791d752f-a2e2-460d-a5ab-37ea5b493fc1.title: Intentional self-harm— shooting
791d752f-a2e2-460d-a5ab-37ea5b493fc1.definition: Intentionally shooting self with a bullet or other projectile from a powder-charged gun, such as handgun, shotgun, or rifle.
791d752f-a2e2-460d-a5ab-37ea5b493fc1.includes: Shot self in suicide or suicide attempt
791d752f-a2e2-460d-a5ab-37ea5b493fc1.excludes: Shot self while cleaning or handling gun (641)

e28c99f6-2ec2-4ae5-a7a0-4bb83eb9505f.title: Intentional self-harm— hanging, strangulation, asphyxiation
e28c99f6-2ec2-4ae5-a7a0-4bb83eb9505f.definition: Choking, strangulation, suffocation, smothering or any other type of asphyxiation by self with intent to harm. Injuries may be inflicted with hands, weapons, or improvised objects.

8072c150-1305-4025-90dc-c87f25654d02.title: Intentional self-harm— jump from building, structure
8072c150-1305-4025-90dc-c87f25654d02.definition: Jumping to a lower level with the intention of harming oneself.
8072c150-1305-4025-90dc-c87f25654d02.includes: Jumping from a structure to a lower level
8072c150-1305-4025-90dc-c87f25654d02.excludes: Jumping to avoid danger or to get to another location (41)

5b974780-e419-48f3-8d31-08f8265b3a78.title: Intentional self-harm— cutting, stabbing
5b974780-e419-48f3-8d31-08f8265b3a78.definition: Stabbing, cutting, slashing or piercing oneself with the intention of self harm. Injuries may be inflicted by actual weapons or improvised objects.

4c5b6342-5be7-46f4-8436-c63b4a2b9179.title: Intentional self-harm— poisoning, drug overdose
4c5b6342-5be7-46f4-8436-c63b4a2b9179.definition: Administration of drugs or poisonous substances by self with harmful intent. Substances can be ingested or taken intravenously.
4c5b6342-5be7-46f4-8436-c63b4a2b9179.includes: Intentional ingestion of drug or poison to harm oneself
4c5b6342-5be7-46f4-8436-c63b4a2b9179.excludes: intentional inhalation of vehicle exhaust to harm oneself

19ed393b-6729-498d-ac74-a6cee6573872.title: Intentional self-harm— n.e.c.
19ed393b-6729-498d-ac74-a6cee6573872.definition: Intentional self harming acts that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes from 121 to 125.
19ed393b-6729-498d-ac74-a6cee6573872.includes: Intentional self-harm from stun gun, BB gun, nail gun, automobile crash, fire, explosion; intentionally hitting oneself or external objects (punching wall, head-butting wall or mirror); self-immolation
19ed393b-6729-498d-ac74-a6cee6573872.excludes: Accidental contact with objects or contact with unknown intent (Division 6)

9cd305a1-1660-4eb0-a7c2-bd395edff3b0.title: Witnessing a violent act
9cd305a1-1660-4eb0-a7c2-bd395edff3b0.definition: Instances where the worker was not a direct victim of violence or under immediate threat of violence, but experienced psychological distress due to witnessing an intentional violent act by another person or the aftermath of such an act.
9cd305a1-1660-4eb0-a7c2-bd395edff3b0.includes: Witnessing a suicide, murder, robbery, etc. in progress; encountering the scene of violence after the event; first responder suffers distress from encountering victims of violent act; witnessing a violent act or the aftermath of a violent act that does not threaten or do physical harm to the worker
9cd305a1-1660-4eb0-a7c2-bd395edff3b0.excludes: Being "held up" or threatened during commission of a robbery or other crime (117); being kidnapped or held hostage without bodily harm (119); being physically injured as a bystander to a violent act (11); witnessing an injury not due to a violent act such as a vehicle accident (57); stress from being present during a violent act by a person which could result in physical harm to the worker, even if no injury occurs (11)

0c01a475-d93c-44fe-b29a-4023166b3136.title: TRANSPORTATION INCIDENTS
0c01a475-d93c-44fe-b29a-4023166b3136.definition: Codes in this division apply to injuries resulting from vehicles in normal operation. Select the appropriate code to reflect the vehicle or conveyance that the injured worker was using at the time of the incident. Vehicles are defined as aircraft, rail, water or motorized and non-motorized land vehicles intended for human occupancy and/or use on roadway or railway systems that are shared with other vehicles transporting people. Mobile equipment, such as tractors and mobile machinery that meet these requirements may also be considered vehicles. Normal operation is defined as forward or backwards motion operating under the control of a person or computerized system at the start of the incident. Vehicles that are moving over the ground surface in an uncontrolled fashion (non-normal operation) are coded in Division 6, Contact. Division 2 also includes injuries to pedestrians, defined as persons who are struck by a vehicles in normal operation but who are not themselves the occupant of any type of vehicle, regardless of their activity or location relative to vehicles in transport at the time of the incident. Vehicle occupants may be fully or partially inside the vehicle or in the process of boarding or alighting the vehicle at the time of the incident.

4045f74a-b13a-422d-8a5b-4813ce1c5ab2.title: Transportation incidents— unspecified
4045f74a-b13a-422d-8a5b-4813ce1c5ab2.definition: Transportation incidents in which the type of vehicle is unknown. If the vehicle was known, but the specific type of incident cannot be determined, defer to order of precedence.
4045f74a-b13a-422d-8a5b-4813ce1c5ab2.excludes: Plane incident (21); boat accident (22); rail accident (23); non-motor vehicle incident (24), pedestrian incident (25); motorized land vehicle accident (26, 27)

ecd7ff61-76dd-4fb0-95ad-409f31ab386a.title: Aircraft incidents
ecd7ff61-76dd-4fb0-95ad-409f31ab386a.definition: Codes in this major group apply to incidents involving aircraft which are in use for transport of persons and goods. Incidents may occur while the aircraft is moving on the ground or through the air. Aircraft are defined as sources in Division 8.

af981832-1535-46b1-bade-4896dda0991d.title: Aircraft incidents— unspecified
af981832-1535-46b1-bade-4896dda0991d.definition: Incident involving an aircraft, but a more detailed code from groups 211 to 219 cannot be determined
af981832-1535-46b1-bade-4896dda0991d.includes: "Worker injured by aircraft" with no further information

3880fb05-550d-4b46-8722-e872e5b045d5.title: Non-passenger struck by aircraft
3880fb05-550d-4b46-8722-e872e5b045d5.definition: Pedestrians struck by aircraft in flight, taxiing aircraft or propeller.
3880fb05-550d-4b46-8722-e872e5b045d5.includes: Worker on tarmac struck by plane taxiing
3880fb05-550d-4b46-8722-e872e5b045d5.excludes: building occupant injured when plane crashes into building

58715962-2602-4874-ac54-6371991ce65a.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing
58715962-2602-4874-ac54-6371991ce65a.definition: Crashes when the aircraft is in the process of preparing to leave the runway, taking off, or landing. This also includes in-flight ascent and descent.

4aba0ee9-278e-4c1c-818a-e383cf01c775.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing— unspecified
4aba0ee9-278e-4c1c-818a-e383cf01c775.definition: Aircraft crashes occurring during takeoff or landing when a more detailed code from 2121 to 2129 cannot be determined.

04d88acf-6a55-436c-8a8e-e93cab3ea24e.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing due to mechanical failure
04d88acf-6a55-436c-8a8e-e93cab3ea24e.definition: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing due to failure of the engine or any other part of the plane
04d88acf-6a55-436c-8a8e-e93cab3ea24e.includes: Fires due to mechanical failure resulting in crashes during takeoff or landing
04d88acf-6a55-436c-8a8e-e93cab3ea24e.excludes: Crashes during takeoff or landing due to any reason except mechanical failure of the aircraft (2122, 2123, 2129)

f1629d57-2316-4557-87e5-9489a26d0b1d.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing between air vehicles
f1629d57-2316-4557-87e5-9489a26d0b1d.definition: Crashes between air vehicles when at least one vehicle is in the process of takeoff or landing. Aircraft may be on the ground or in the air at the time of impact.
f1629d57-2316-4557-87e5-9489a26d0b1d.includes: Collision between aircrafts on the runway
f1629d57-2316-4557-87e5-9489a26d0b1d.excludes: Mid air collisions when neither aircraft is taking off or landing (213)

f56168b3-356f-494b-b4c1-90f4557289cd.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing into structure, object, or ground
f56168b3-356f-494b-b4c1-90f4557289cd.definition: Aircraft crashes occurring during takeoff or landing when the aircraft crashes into an object or surface other than another aircraft.
f56168b3-356f-494b-b4c1-90f4557289cd.includes: Crash into ground, mountain, building, trees, power lines, or body of water during takeoff or landing

27389f95-019a-4280-b27a-57533f99eeee.title: Aircraft crash during takeoff or landing— n.e.c.
27389f95-019a-4280-b27a-57533f99eeee.definition: Aircraft crashes in which the event is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 2120 to 2123.

c9f89d38-ca9c-4b41-a934-3da0654da1ff.title: In-flight crash, collision
c9f89d38-ca9c-4b41-a934-3da0654da1ff.excludes: Crashes during takeoff or landing, ascent or descent (212); non-passengers struck by aircraft (211)

8e6d654e-f372-48a6-9355-28d1897d0a32.title: In-flight crash— unspecified
8e6d654e-f372-48a6-9355-28d1897d0a32.definition: Aircraft crashes occurring during flight when a more detailed code from 2131 to 2139 cannot be determined

1f208fff-756c-458b-a918-971d31a2ffab.title: In-flight crash due to mechanical failure
1f208fff-756c-458b-a918-971d31a2ffab.definition: In flight aircraft crashes occurring due to mechanical failure of the aircraft.
1f208fff-756c-458b-a918-971d31a2ffab.excludes: In flight crashes due to any reason except mechanical failure of the aircraft (2132, 2133, 2139);  in flight crash due to mechanical failure during takeoff or landing (2121)

edb3641c-be20-4ddb-9306-71237b6c18f5.title: In-flight collision between air vehicles
edb3641c-be20-4ddb-9306-71237b6c18f5.definition: Crashes between air vehicles when both vehicles are in flight.
edb3641c-be20-4ddb-9306-71237b6c18f5.includes: Plane and helicopter in flight crash
edb3641c-be20-4ddb-9306-71237b6c18f5.excludes: Crashes due to mechanical failure (2131); crash during takeoff or landing (212); single aircraft in-flight crash (2131, 2133, 2199)

ac5aaba5-0c44-4c6a-8d4e-c18cfb950480.title: Low altitude entanglement
ac5aaba5-0c44-4c6a-8d4e-c18cfb950480.definition: Aircraft crashes and other incidents resulting from the aircraft becoming entangled with trees or power lines at low altitude.
ac5aaba5-0c44-4c6a-8d4e-c18cfb950480.excludes: helicopter crash resulting from items being carried snagging on a tree

f9002652-6e3c-4bd8-b8b3-346fa0a48caf.title: In-flight crash, collision into structure, object, ground— n.e.c.
f9002652-6e3c-4bd8-b8b3-346fa0a48caf.definition: Aircraft crashes in which the event is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 2130 to 2133.
f9002652-6e3c-4bd8-b8b3-346fa0a48caf.includes: Bird strike; crash into mountain, building, trees

256244c2-1897-48f3-a990-af5714f96cdf.title: Incidents onboard aircraft in normal operation
256244c2-1897-48f3-a990-af5714f96cdf.definition: Incidents occurring onboard an aircraft that is moving along the ground or in flight that are not the result of an impending crash.
256244c2-1897-48f3-a990-af5714f96cdf.includes: Injuries resulting from in-flight turbulence or sudden drop in altitude
256244c2-1897-48f3-a990-af5714f96cdf.excludes: Any type of collision or crash (212-213); injuries onboard aircraft that is parked, not in transport (code to appropriate division)

bb7dfece-cbf8-4d96-9fcd-82030ba21dbc.title: Incidents onboard aircraft in normal operation— unspecified
bb7dfece-cbf8-4d96-9fcd-82030ba21dbc.definition: Incidents occurring onboard aircraft in normal operation but a more detailed code from 2141 to 2149 cannot be determined.

ce22b73d-8775-4534-ae5d-1b255cc32ee0.title: Fires, explosions onboard aircraft in normal operation
ce22b73d-8775-4534-ae5d-1b255cc32ee0.definition: Small scale fires and explosions resulting from machinery or cargo onboard the aircraft that are not the result of a crash or failure of the aircraft itself.

35e77770-5b34-4d36-bbf6-c6722a3b5ee5.title: Fall, contact incident onboard aircraft in normal operation
35e77770-5b34-4d36-bbf6-c6722a3b5ee5.definition: Falls, slips, trips, or contact with objects or equipment while onboard aircraft in transport without a crash incident.
35e77770-5b34-4d36-bbf6-c6722a3b5ee5.includes: Falls due to turbulence or sudden drop in altitude; any slip, trip or fall on an aircraft in motion; struck by shifting cargo; equipment or machinery incidents in flight; contact due to turbulence

2b40c82d-ecba-4306-aebb-bb973735d155.title: Exposure incident onboard aircraft in normal operation
2b40c82d-ecba-4306-aebb-bb973735d155.definition: Exposure to harmful substances or environments while onboard aircraft in transport without a crash incident.
2b40c82d-ecba-4306-aebb-bb973735d155.includes: Oxygen deprivation from loss of cabin pressure

d41f4539-36c6-4a68-a247-23a0e47c5982.title: Overexertion incidents onboard aircraft in normal operation
d41f4539-36c6-4a68-a247-23a0e47c5982.definition: Overexertions or bodily motion incidents occurring while onboard aircraft in transport without a crash incident.
d41f4539-36c6-4a68-a247-23a0e47c5982.includes: Bodily motion injuries due to turbulence

7e2a2eca-32c3-4c01-b6ac-c21cc716ab4f.title: Parachuting and nonpowered aircraft incidents
7e2a2eca-32c3-4c01-b6ac-c21cc716ab4f.definition: Incidents resulting from planned use of parachutes or nonpowered aircraft (e.g. hang gliders).
7e2a2eca-32c3-4c01-b6ac-c21cc716ab4f.excludes: striking an object or other person while in the air or upon landing

3996a861-9a4a-4637-96fb-074057ff4d2b.title: Other aircraft incident— n.e.c.
3996a861-9a4a-4637-96fb-074057ff4d2b.definition: Incidents involving aircraft that are known but does not fit descriptions of event code groups 210 to 215.

6a0fdc78-11d0-4d7e-8445-cd909d460ae5.title: Water vehicle incidents
6a0fdc78-11d0-4d7e-8445-cd909d460ae5.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries resulting from water vehicle crashes, collisions, incidents occurring to passengers while riding on water vessels or nonpassengers, such as swimmers and divers, who are struck by water vessels. Water vessels must meet definition of normal operation for the event to meet the definition of Transportation. Incidents occurring onboard docked water vessels (wet or dry dock) are not considered transportation cases. Water vehicles are defined as sources in Division 8.
6a0fdc78-11d0-4d7e-8445-cd909d460ae5.excludes: incidents occurring to passengers while onboard water vessel underway such as falls and machinery accidents

3e94d36c-d92e-4d02-ab42-8bc3e5384979.title: Water vehicle incidents— unspecified
3e94d36c-d92e-4d02-ab42-8bc3e5384979.definition: Incidents involving water vehicles when a more detailed code from groups 221 to 229 cannot be determined.
3e94d36c-d92e-4d02-ab42-8bc3e5384979.includes: Descriptions of "boating incident" with no further information
3e94d36c-d92e-4d02-ab42-8bc3e5384979.excludes: Incidents on docked water vehicles (may code in any Event division)

7a22664e-6b62-4cde-94e4-887d255cc27d.title: Non-passenger struck by water vehicle
7a22664e-6b62-4cde-94e4-887d255cc27d.definition: Incidents involving water vehicles injuring persons who were not passengers of the vessel that produced the injury or any other type of vehicle. Includes injuries to swimmers and divers
7a22664e-6b62-4cde-94e4-887d255cc27d.includes: all persons who voluntarily alighted from a water vessel
7a22664e-6b62-4cde-94e4-887d255cc27d.excludes: and persons working on docks or around water vehicles.

2e7bba7d-9cb2-496e-a2bf-be799065e11b.title: Water vehicle collisions
2e7bba7d-9cb2-496e-a2bf-be799065e11b.definition: Incidents involving a water vehicle striking a solid object or another water vessel.
2e7bba7d-9cb2-496e-a2bf-be799065e11b.includes: Fires resulting from water vessel collisions; capsized or sinking water vehicle as a result of a collision; incidents involving water vessels that are anchored, but not docked
2e7bba7d-9cb2-496e-a2bf-be799065e11b.excludes: Capsized or sinking water vehicle without collision (223); pedestrian struck by water vehicle or propeller (221); "collisions" with waves (223)

1fd35e18-7e01-43b3-85e8-55404700acb7.title: Water vehicle collision— unspecified
1fd35e18-7e01-43b3-85e8-55404700acb7.definition: Water vehicle collisions when information about the object struck (codes 2221-2229) cannot be determined.
1fd35e18-7e01-43b3-85e8-55404700acb7.includes: Descriptions of water vehicle collisions without information about what was struck, i.e. "jet ski collision"

e667d784-b2c0-42d5-ae8d-a27379a3f5c9.title: Collision between water vehicles
e667d784-b2c0-42d5-ae8d-a27379a3f5c9.definition: Collisions between water vehicles of any size or type.

4df7995f-25a7-4c41-9913-4ffa6dae20d8.title: Collision between water vehicle and object(s)— n.e.c.
4df7995f-25a7-4c41-9913-4ffa6dae20d8.definition: Incidents involving a water vehicle striking a solid object other than another water vessel.
4df7995f-25a7-4c41-9913-4ffa6dae20d8.includes: Water vehicle striking buoy, iceberg, or other floating object; water vehicle striking stationary object(s) such as rocks, bridge structures, piers or pilings

4c48b8df-b06b-4aae-81bc-858b2b18ec06.title: Capsized or sinking water vehicle (non collision)
4c48b8df-b06b-4aae-81bc-858b2b18ec06.definition: Water vehicle sinking or capsizing due to any reason except a collision with another vehicle or solid object.
4c48b8df-b06b-4aae-81bc-858b2b18ec06.includes: Sinking vessel due to a structural defect not related to a collision

37f56cb9-cab6-4003-84c5-d66e6674de68.title: Incidents onboard water vehicle in normal operation
37f56cb9-cab6-4003-84c5-d66e6674de68.definition: Incidents onboard a water vehicle in water in the absence of a collision or sinking.
37f56cb9-cab6-4003-84c5-d66e6674de68.includes: Jumps from water vehicle in distress
37f56cb9-cab6-4003-84c5-d66e6674de68.excludes: Jumps from water vehicle with intention of self harm (123)

b1dbbaee-fe8e-4ca7-9c90-a88c970a226f.title: Incidents onboard water vehicle in normal operation— unspecified
b1dbbaee-fe8e-4ca7-9c90-a88c970a226f.definition: Incidents on a water vehicle in water when a more detailed code from 2241 to 2246 cannot be determined.
b1dbbaee-fe8e-4ca7-9c90-a88c970a226f.excludes: Incident caused by a collision or sinking of a water vehicle (222-223)

23c28858-5507-4792-97dd-cba377e0364a.title: Fires, explosions onboard water vehicle in normal operation
23c28858-5507-4792-97dd-cba377e0364a.definition: Fires and explosions resulting from machinery or cargo onboard the water vehicle that are not the result of a collision.

af792748-1b0c-4cdb-800b-aefe69e99653.title: Fall, jump from water vehicle
af792748-1b0c-4cdb-800b-aefe69e99653.definition: Falling or involuntarily jumping overboard from a water vehicle, without being struck by a water vessel
af792748-1b0c-4cdb-800b-aefe69e99653.excludes: Injuries to swimmers or divers who voluntarily jump from a water vessel (221)

463ca760-2910-4329-8efe-e1470fe99fcb.title: Fall, jump from and struck by water vehicle
463ca760-2910-4329-8efe-e1470fe99fcb.definition: Falling or involuntarily jumping overboard from a water vehicle and struck by a water vessel.
463ca760-2910-4329-8efe-e1470fe99fcb.includes: Fall from and struck by same water vehicle or another water vehicle
463ca760-2910-4329-8efe-e1470fe99fcb.excludes: Fall from water vehicle without being struck by water vehicle (2242)

490c85b5-351d-4339-9fab-973fb5ff8605.title: Fall, contact incident onboard water vehicle
490c85b5-351d-4339-9fab-973fb5ff8605.definition: Injuries resulting from falls on same level or to lower level or contact with objects, equipment while onboard water vehicle in water
490c85b5-351d-4339-9fab-973fb5ff8605.includes: Fall on water vessel docked in water

fb16d95c-f4e7-441e-9c70-1a4054ec9fb6.title: Exposure incident onboard water vehicle in normal operation
fb16d95c-f4e7-441e-9c70-1a4054ec9fb6.definition: Exposure to harmful substances or environments while onboard a water vehicle in normal operation without a crash incident.
fb16d95c-f4e7-441e-9c70-1a4054ec9fb6.includes: Oxygen deprivation from loss of cabin pressure

9754476f-6a0b-4a96-bf87-5e47ac326a31.title: Overexertion incidents onboard water vehicle in normal operation
9754476f-6a0b-4a96-bf87-5e47ac326a31.definition: Overexertions or bodily motion incidents occurring while onboard a water vehicle in normal operation without a crash incident.
9754476f-6a0b-4a96-bf87-5e47ac326a31.includes: Bodily motion injuries due to turbulence

ba9356f8-9dac-449a-86d6-8301d9bfcaf9.title: Other water vehicle incident n.e.c.
ba9356f8-9dac-449a-86d6-8301d9bfcaf9.definition: Incidents involving water vessel(s) that are known but does not fit descriptions of event code groups 220 to 224.

180c3373-68b8-4d59-b5b0-0ffb7a4fddfa.title: Rail vehicle incidents
180c3373-68b8-4d59-b5b0-0ffb7a4fddfa.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of rail vehicle incident involving least one rail vehicle in transportation operations
180c3373-68b8-4d59-b5b0-0ffb7a4fddfa.includes: Full size passenger and freight trains

00434155-99e2-4590-af50-58cf31231793.title: Rail vehicle incident— unspecified
00434155-99e2-4590-af50-58cf31231793.definition: Incidents involving at least one rail vehicle when a more detailed code from 231 to 239 cannot be determined.

3050b0bf-c293-4b24-81f9-ab6470297334.title: Non-passenger struck by rail vehicle
3050b0bf-c293-4b24-81f9-ab6470297334.definition: Pedestrians struck by rail vehicle, excluding passengers who fall or jump from a rail vehicle.
3050b0bf-c293-4b24-81f9-ab6470297334.includes: Track workers hit by oncoming train
3050b0bf-c293-4b24-81f9-ab6470297334.excludes: Struck by rail vehicle after falling or jumping from a rail vehicle (2343)

1141ce80-3b4a-4735-bfb5-4bbaada2107f.title: Rail vehicle collisions
1141ce80-3b4a-4735-bfb5-4bbaada2107f.definition: Collisions of rail vehicles with other vehicles, objects, or equipment.

ba43ced4-30b0-4ac9-bfae-1e1bfdb6c94c.title: Rail vehicle collision— unspecified
ba43ced4-30b0-4ac9-bfae-1e1bfdb6c94c.definition: Collisions of rail vehicles when the object(s) collided with in detailed codes 2321 through 2329 cannot be determined
ba43ced4-30b0-4ac9-bfae-1e1bfdb6c94c.excludes: Derailment not resulting from a collision (233)

9231ce8e-5a53-46be-9abd-e56b9cd3a252.title: Collision between rail vehicles
9231ce8e-5a53-46be-9abd-e56b9cd3a252.definition: Collisions between rail vehicles, including train engines, attached or unattached rail cars or other rail mounted vehicles or equipment.
9231ce8e-5a53-46be-9abd-e56b9cd3a252.includes: Moving train hits stopped rail car on tracks

f90d1317-4fc8-4883-b97d-917c2f972efd.title: Collision between rail and roadway vehicles
f90d1317-4fc8-4883-b97d-917c2f972efd.definition: Collision between rail vehicle and motorized or non-motorized land vehicle(s)
f90d1317-4fc8-4883-b97d-917c2f972efd.includes: Collision between train and roadway vehicle stalled on rails

cbc1480b-a541-42f5-9d1a-096b25ed1a8d.title: Collision between rail vehicle and object(s)— n.e.c.
cbc1480b-a541-42f5-9d1a-096b25ed1a8d.definition: Injuries resulting from collisions between rail vehicles and objects or animals, except other rail vehicles or roadway vehicles.
cbc1480b-a541-42f5-9d1a-096b25ed1a8d.includes: Train strikes tree down on rails

1e52a2c5-e03d-4a28-ae5a-06670d58c2f6.title: Non-collision derailment
1e52a2c5-e03d-4a28-ae5a-06670d58c2f6.definition: Incidents where railway vehicles leave the rails for reasons other than collision with object or other vehicles on the rails. If a rail vehicle collides with object or structure after leaving the rails, it would still be coded here.
1e52a2c5-e03d-4a28-ae5a-06670d58c2f6.includes: Derailment resulting from a track problem or mechanical problem with the train
1e52a2c5-e03d-4a28-ae5a-06670d58c2f6.excludes: derailments caused by hard braking to avoid a collision

c19b0f10-128a-45b7-8fce-9d6278626866.title: Incidents onboard rail vehicle in normal operation
c19b0f10-128a-45b7-8fce-9d6278626866.definition: Incidents occurring as a result of normal starts and stops and regular motion of the train

ddd4ee93-ccff-4a1c-90ab-cd4af259f4ee.title: Incident onboard rail vehicle in normal operation— unspecified
ddd4ee93-ccff-4a1c-90ab-cd4af259f4ee.definition: Incident occurring onboard rail vehicles that are not in the process of crashing or derailing when a more detailed code from 2341 to 2349 cannot be determined

f8cb2f9b-c0f4-4cb0-ae1b-b5cf74cf6b02.title: Fire, explosion onboard rail vehicles in normal operation
f8cb2f9b-c0f4-4cb0-ae1b-b5cf74cf6b02.definition: Small scale fires and explosions resulting from machinery or cargo onboard the rail vehicle that are not the result of a collision or failure of the vehicle itself.
f8cb2f9b-c0f4-4cb0-ae1b-b5cf74cf6b02.excludes: Fire as a result of a collision (232) or derailment (233)

d3cf0d51-1074-4c9c-b70c-ae9ac69abd12.title: Fall, jump from rail vehicle
d3cf0d51-1074-4c9c-b70c-ae9ac69abd12.definition: Falling or involuntarily jumping from a rail vehicle without a collision, derailment or sudden stop or start.
d3cf0d51-1074-4c9c-b70c-ae9ac69abd12.includes: Person falls from train in motion
d3cf0d51-1074-4c9c-b70c-ae9ac69abd12.excludes: Jump or push from rail vehicle to intentionally harm self or other person (Division 1)

f2dd114b-b67e-47a7-8f2f-3e87a4cdb309.title: Fall, jump from and struck by rail vehicle
f2dd114b-b67e-47a7-8f2f-3e87a4cdb309.definition: Falling or involuntarily jumping from a rail vehicle and struck by the same or different rail vehicle without a collision, derailment or sudden stop or start.
f2dd114b-b67e-47a7-8f2f-3e87a4cdb309.includes: Conductor falls from train and is struck by a train
f2dd114b-b67e-47a7-8f2f-3e87a4cdb309.excludes: Jump or push from rail vehicle to intentionally harm self or other person (Division 1); fall or jump from rail vehicle as a result of collision (232), derailment (233) or sudden stop or start (234);

0bac32cf-3acf-4aa6-892a-573c734803a5.title: Fall, contact incident onboard rail vehicle in normal operation
0bac32cf-3acf-4aa6-892a-573c734803a5.definition: Falls, slips, trips, or contact with objects or equipment while onboard rail vehicle in transport without a collision, derailment or sudden stop or start.
0bac32cf-3acf-4aa6-892a-573c734803a5.includes: Person falls on subway while it is in motion
0bac32cf-3acf-4aa6-892a-573c734803a5.excludes: falls as a result of sudden stops and starts

a1a8c23a-8276-44bd-b8aa-50bed3c89b43.title: Exposure incident onboard rail vehicle in normal operation
a1a8c23a-8276-44bd-b8aa-50bed3c89b43.definition: Exposure to harmful substances or environments while onboard a rail vehicle in normal operation without a crash incident.

4d16f839-43a9-4332-8f5b-c862f24279a5.title: Overexertion incidents onboard rail vehicle in normal operation
4d16f839-43a9-4332-8f5b-c862f24279a5.definition: Overexertions or bodily motion incidents occurring while onboard a rail vehicle in normal operation without a crash incident.
4d16f839-43a9-4332-8f5b-c862f24279a5.includes: Bodily motion injuries due to vehicle motion

9b081c0a-cc08-4154-8934-bcc38a934d27.title: Incident onboard rail vehicles— n.e.c.
9b081c0a-cc08-4154-8934-bcc38a934d27.definition: Incidents occurring onboard a rail vehicle that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 2341 to 2346.

d1fd931a-6350-4035-a46c-092769bc8792.title: Other rail vehicle incident— n.e.c.
d1fd931a-6350-4035-a46c-092769bc8792.definition: Incidents involving water vessel(s) that are known but does not fit descriptions of event codes in groups 230 to 234.

7b494010-3d03-421a-8ec6-c26997d7e04e.title: Non-motorized transport incidents
7b494010-3d03-421a-8ec6-c26997d7e04e.definition: Codes in this major group apply to incidents in which the injured worker was in transport via a ridden animal; animal-powered vehicle; or human powered vehicle such as a pedal cycle or rickshaw. Ski incidents are also captured here. Injuries resulting from other non-pedal personal conveyance including rollerblades, scooters and skateboards that do not involve collision with another transportation vehicle should be coded in the appropriate division according to the details of the incidents.
7b494010-3d03-421a-8ec6-c26997d7e04e.excludes: Incidents in which the animal was neither being ridden nor used to pull a vehicle, such as collisions with deer in the roadway (2622); injuries resulting from non-pedal personal conveyance including rollerblades, scooters and skateboards that do not involve collision with another transportation vehicle (code in appropriate Event division)

32e8f7ba-0ac7-41a4-aec2-522d499f4d4d.title: Non-motorized transport incident— unspecified
32e8f7ba-0ac7-41a4-aec2-522d499f4d4d.definition: Incidents involving non-motorized transport when a more detailed code from groups 241 to 249 cannot be determined.
32e8f7ba-0ac7-41a4-aec2-522d499f4d4d.excludes: Pedestrians struck by motorized vehicles and equipment (25)

605e7b1c-9115-4055-b95d-230eb4c2ea15.title: Animal transportation incidents
605e7b1c-9115-4055-b95d-230eb4c2ea15.definition: Codes in this group include injuries resulting from all types of animals being ridden or to pull non-motorized conveyance.
605e7b1c-9115-4055-b95d-230eb4c2ea15.includes: Injuries while riding animals in entertainment or competitive events, i.e. rodeos, dressage events, circuses (2413); injuries while traveling in animal-drawn conveyance; dog sledding
605e7b1c-9115-4055-b95d-230eb4c2ea15.excludes: Animals hitched to a plow when the plow is not being ridden (Division 6)

8a463199-40d4-492b-9d75-e27394b51132.title: Animal transportation incidents— unspecified
8a463199-40d4-492b-9d75-e27394b51132.definition: Incidents involving animal transport when a more detailed code from 2411 to 2419 cannot be determined.

06f00761-b337-468b-ba87-04eab465ebdd.title: Animal transportation collision in roadway
06f00761-b337-468b-ba87-04eab465ebdd.definition: Incidents where persons riding animals or animal-drawn transportation collide with or are struck by land vehicles, in roadway areas. Roadway incidents occur on any part of publicly maintained traffic ways intended for motorized land vehicle travel, including roadway, shoulders, medians, surrounding areas etc.
06f00761-b337-468b-ba87-04eab465ebdd.includes: Mounted police officer struck by car in roadway
06f00761-b337-468b-ba87-04eab465ebdd.excludes: car rear-ends horse drawn buggy in roadway

913c70cf-09bb-4fac-9f6d-b2a6796adbeb.title: Animal transportation collision in nonroadway area
913c70cf-09bb-4fac-9f6d-b2a6796adbeb.definition: Incidents where persons riding animals or animal-drawn transportation collide with or are struck by land vehicles, in nonroadway areas. Nonroadway incidents occur on private and commercial roadways, sidewalks, driveways, fields, arenas, and parking lots
913c70cf-09bb-4fac-9f6d-b2a6796adbeb.includes: horse drawn wagon collides with haystack in a field
913c70cf-09bb-4fac-9f6d-b2a6796adbeb.excludes: Collisions between ridden animals during sporting events

5e681865-2aa5-4d8e-9564-1b5adb8cce09.title: Thrown, fell, or jumped from animal transportation
5e681865-2aa5-4d8e-9564-1b5adb8cce09.definition: Incidents where the rider was thrown, fell or jumped from and animal being ridden or animal drawn vehicle in any location.
5e681865-2aa5-4d8e-9564-1b5adb8cce09.includes: Horse rider is thrown on a public road
5e681865-2aa5-4d8e-9564-1b5adb8cce09.excludes: rider bucked from horse during rodeo

398adcee-7d65-4311-a02e-2ac0a42a1a26.title: Animal transportation incident— n.e.c.
398adcee-7d65-4311-a02e-2ac0a42a1a26.definition: Incidents involving animal transport that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes from 2410 to 2413.
398adcee-7d65-4311-a02e-2ac0a42a1a26.includes: Struck bump, hole or rough terrain without falling from animal transport

6fa693f3-55f6-432e-9eaa-c751ffd7f00e.title: Pedal cycle incidents
6fa693f3-55f6-432e-9eaa-c751ffd7f00e.definition: Incidents resulting in injuries to pedal cyclists and pedestrians struck by cyclists.
6fa693f3-55f6-432e-9eaa-c751ffd7f00e.includes: Bicycles, electric assist bikes, tricycles, unicycles, rickshaws, etc.
6fa693f3-55f6-432e-9eaa-c751ffd7f00e.excludes: Overexertion injuries due to cycling, unless a crash is involved (71)

fbae138e-9910-4eb9-9966-283a9f053699.title: Pedal cycle incidents— unspecified
fbae138e-9910-4eb9-9966-283a9f053699.definition: Incidents resulting injuries to pedal cyclists when a more detailed code from 2421 to 2429 cannot be determined.

b1a4e62c-2886-4422-b6d8-80740f9c5747.title: Pedal cycle collision in roadway
b1a4e62c-2886-4422-b6d8-80740f9c5747.definition: Incidents where pedal cyclists collide with or are struck by other land vehicles, in roadway areas. Roadway incidents occur on any part of publicly maintained traffic ways intended for motorized land vehicle travel, including roadway, shoulders, medians, surrounding areas etc.
b1a4e62c-2886-4422-b6d8-80740f9c5747.includes: Cyclist hit by car in bike lane on side of road
b1a4e62c-2886-4422-b6d8-80740f9c5747.excludes: fall off of bike and struck by car in roadway

f86df979-da20-41f3-bd1d-5963672e9b1b.title: Pedal cycle collision in nonroadway area
f86df979-da20-41f3-bd1d-5963672e9b1b.definition: Incidents where pedal cyclists collide with or are struck by other land vehicles, in nonroadway areas. Nonroadway incidents occur on private and commercial roadways, sidewalks, driveways, fields, arenas, and parking lots
f86df979-da20-41f3-bd1d-5963672e9b1b.includes: Cyclist hit by car on sidewalk; fall from bike and hit by car, nonroadway; bicycle hits another bicycle on the street; pedi cab hits a tree on the sidewalk; pedestrian struck by cyclist

6961652d-8f69-4e59-bb06-933a03b44763.title: Fall from pedal cycle
6961652d-8f69-4e59-bb06-933a03b44763.definition: Falls from pedal powered vehicles in any location except as a result of a collision.
6961652d-8f69-4e59-bb06-933a03b44763.includes: Bicycle rider falls in street or field
6961652d-8f69-4e59-bb06-933a03b44763.excludes: Pedal cycle rider falls as a result of collision (2421, 2422); fall from a bike and subsequently hit by motorized vehicle (2421, 2422)

971da483-e38a-465f-9ef6-a1ab6d6f3e8b.title: Pedal cycle incident— n.e.c.
971da483-e38a-465f-9ef6-a1ab6d6f3e8b.definition: Incidents involving pedal cycles that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes from 2421 to 2423.
971da483-e38a-465f-9ef6-a1ab6d6f3e8b.includes: Pedal cyclist jarred or vibrated from striking bump, hole, or other rough terrain without falling
971da483-e38a-465f-9ef6-a1ab6d6f3e8b.excludes: Bicycle rider falls from striking bump hole or rough terrain (2423)

8b403841-f482-4e83-a3f2-fa733d360226.title: Ski, snowboard, and sled incidents
8b403841-f482-4e83-a3f2-fa733d360226.definition: All types of ski incidents including when a worker is using skis as a mode of transportation, providing ski instruction, or for competition. It also includes non-skiers who are struck by other persons using snow conveyance.
8b403841-f482-4e83-a3f2-fa733d360226.includes: Snowboarding incidents; injuries from hypothermia after ski crash, sledding and toboggan incidents
8b403841-f482-4e83-a3f2-fa733d360226.excludes: Overexertion injuries due to skiing unless there is a crash involved (71); dog sledding (241); curling; ice-skating (code to type of incident, e.g. falls or contact); horse-drawn sleigh (241)

de46a072-8a85-496f-86a5-bf4c72da4a29.title: Ski, snowboard, and sled incidents— unspecified
de46a072-8a85-496f-86a5-bf4c72da4a29.definition: Incidents occurring while skiing when a more detailed code from 2431 to 2439 cannot be determined.

145557fb-1f77-4e18-8930-329663e45308.title: Collision on skis, snowboard, sled
145557fb-1f77-4e18-8930-329663e45308.definition: Incidents where the motion of the injured skier produced impact with any person, object, or equipment that is greater than a ground irregularity while skiing or was struck by another skier or vehicle in transport.
145557fb-1f77-4e18-8930-329663e45308.includes: Collision with other skier or non-skier
145557fb-1f77-4e18-8930-329663e45308.excludes: collision with object such as tree

e760577f-ad65-40b2-8062-13fe9c8568f4.title: Struck, engulfed by falling object(s) on skis, snowboard, sled
e760577f-ad65-40b2-8062-13fe9c8568f4.definition: Incidents where a skier is struck by a moving object other than a person or vehicle in transport while skiing or standing still on skis.
e760577f-ad65-40b2-8062-13fe9c8568f4.excludes: struck by falling object (e.g. tree) while skiing

97059694-95cc-477c-a8ba-ce93820dbee1.title: Fall from skis, snowboard, sled
97059694-95cc-477c-a8ba-ce93820dbee1.definition: Incidents where a skier falls to the same or lower level in any location and is not the result of a collision or being struck by a non-transport object.

0ad8b368-7675-422b-b473-a18ec330519c.title: Ski, snowboard, and sled incidents— n.e.c.
0ad8b368-7675-422b-b473-a18ec330519c.definition: Incidents occurring while skiing that are known but do not fit descriptions of events 2431 through 2433.

c8b68f5c-dbb9-4e7d-85de-66d5ba660fa1.title: Non-motorized transport incidents— n.e.c.
c8b68f5c-dbb9-4e7d-85de-66d5ba660fa1.definition: Incidents involving non-motorized transport that do not meet descriptions of codes in groups 240 to 243. Injuries resulting from other non-pedal personal conveyance including rollerblades, scooters and skateboards that do not involve collision with another transportation vehicle should be coded in the appropriate division according to the details of the incidents.

f0bd87df-fcd8-4630-b4bb-c200fdbf9977.title: Pedestrian incidents involving motorized land vehicles
f0bd87df-fcd8-4630-b4bb-c200fdbf9977.definition: Codes in this major group apply to pedestrians (non-vehicle occupants) and users of personal conveyance who are struck by traveling motorized land vehicles or other mobile equipment. Locations cited in the code title, refer to the location of the pedestrian at the time of the event and not the location of the vehicle. Personal conveyance is defined as any motorized or non-motorized transport or mobility assistance that is not deemed roadway compliant.
f0bd87df-fcd8-4630-b4bb-c200fdbf9977.includes: land vehicle striking building or structure; pedestrians struck while in motorized or non-motorized personal mobility device, including wheelchairs and motorized scooters; pedestrians struck by vehicles while using skateboards, rollerblades, or other non-roadway compliant personal conveyance
f0bd87df-fcd8-4630-b4bb-c200fdbf9977.excludes: nonpassengers struck by aircraft, watercraft and rail vehicles and non-motorized modes of transport (21-24); vehicle occupants, including persons who fall or are ejected from and struck by vehicle (26, 27);  vehicle occupants injured as a result of the vehicle hitting a pedestrian; persons exiting/entering vehicles or partially inside vehicles and persons riding on vehicle exterior or in exterior cargo areas. (26, 27) ; incidents associated solely with vehicles and mobile equipment that was not in normal operation at the time such as being struck by rising forklifts or falling trailer doors; walking into a parked car (6); pedestrians struck by non-motorized vehicles, (i.e. bikes, skis or animals being ridden) (24)

ce29f95a-2b7f-4889-9bd2-0c26c92d8b77.title: Pedestrian incidents involving motorized land vehicles— unspecified
ce29f95a-2b7f-4889-9bd2-0c26c92d8b77.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by motorized land vehicles when the location in relation to the roadway as specified in codes 251 to 259 is unknown

b838b42e-5ca1-478e-b52d-90b2569d9bfa.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle or object propelled by another vehicle— location unspecified
b838b42e-5ca1-478e-b52d-90b2569d9bfa.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by an object or other vehicle propelled by a motorized land vehicle when relation to the roadway is unknown.

6ccd93cf-fb39-4767-a349-07504fd2d311.title: Pedestrian struck by forward-moving vehicle— location unspecified
6ccd93cf-fb39-4767-a349-07504fd2d311.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by forward moving work vehicles when relation to the roadway is unknown.

3820c141-d129-4c69-9ca5-8af630eacd49.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle backing up—location unspecified
3820c141-d129-4c69-9ca5-8af630eacd49.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by backward moving motorized land vehicles when relation to the roadway is unknown.

e48e7be6-5bc7-452a-92fc-0c7e5faf5259.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle, location unspecified— n.e.c.
e48e7be6-5bc7-452a-92fc-0c7e5faf5259.definition: Pedestrians struck in work zones events that are known but do not fit descriptions of events 2501 to 2503.

186eb4de-f987-48a2-91bd-71956d321bfe.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in road work zone
186eb4de-f987-48a2-91bd-71956d321bfe.definition: Pedestrians struck in the vicinity of public road construction, maintenance, or utility work or within an area marked by signs, barricades, or other devices.
186eb4de-f987-48a2-91bd-71956d321bfe.includes: Injuries during construction or maintenance of highway structures such as guardrails or ditches, surveying activity, pavement marking, painting, cleaning, or mowing grass; directing traffic, flagging or erecting barricades in the work zone
186eb4de-f987-48a2-91bd-71956d321bfe.excludes: Pedestrians struck in non-roadway construction area (253); construction of private roads, lanes or parking lots (253); pedestrians struck by vehicles in non-normal operation (Division 6)

7d89a2a1-a8b3-49a6-b004-45ed99944fb8.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in road work zone— unspecified
7d89a2a1-a8b3-49a6-b004-45ed99944fb8.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by motorized land vehicles in work zones when the detailed cause of the injury specified in codes 2511 to 2519 is unknown
7d89a2a1-a8b3-49a6-b004-45ed99944fb8.includes: Flagger struck in road construction zone
7d89a2a1-a8b3-49a6-b004-45ed99944fb8.excludes: Worker struck at a building construction site (253)

2e63f5dd-e70f-43eb-9ae6-e8992ece51c8.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle or object propelled by another vehicle in road work zone
2e63f5dd-e70f-43eb-9ae6-e8992ece51c8.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by an object or other vehicle propelled by a motorized land vehicle in a work zone, regardless of whether the vehicle was part of the work detail or a vehicle passing the work zone.
2e63f5dd-e70f-43eb-9ae6-e8992ece51c8.includes: Struck by a barrel that was propelled by a truck
2e63f5dd-e70f-43eb-9ae6-e8992ece51c8.excludes: truck strikes a car and pushes it into worker

b8480639-43e1-4600-8c52-a2c777e24568.title: Pedestrian struck by forward-moving vehicle in road work zone
b8480639-43e1-4600-8c52-a2c777e24568.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by forward moving work vehicles in work zones.
b8480639-43e1-4600-8c52-a2c777e24568.includes: Worker in road construction lane struck by oncoming vehicle
b8480639-43e1-4600-8c52-a2c777e24568.excludes: Forward moving vehicle in public roadway (252) or non roadway location (253)

bd13473b-e3d4-44e8-b7d6-1e3284481c29.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle backing up in road work zone
bd13473b-e3d4-44e8-b7d6-1e3284481c29.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by backward moving motorized land vehicles in work zones.
bd13473b-e3d4-44e8-b7d6-1e3284481c29.includes: Dump truck backing over road construction crew on shoulder
bd13473b-e3d4-44e8-b7d6-1e3284481c29.excludes: Backward moving vehicle in public roadway (252) or non roadway location (253)

1f9dc945-9f20-4080-8153-ae1b3c9ae144.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in road work zone— n.e.c.
1f9dc945-9f20-4080-8153-ae1b3c9ae144.definition: Pedestrians struck in work zones events that are known but do not fit descriptions of events 2511 to 2513.

14e3ea7b-e67c-4e74-82f1-254a11e5266e.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in roadway
14e3ea7b-e67c-4e74-82f1-254a11e5266e.definition: Pedestrians and nonoccupants of vehicles who are struck while moving in and around a public roadway. Roadway incidents include any part of publicly maintained traffic ways intended for motorized land vehicle travel, including lanes, shoulders, medians, surrounding areas etc. It excludes private and commercial roadways, driveways, fields, sidewalks, and parking lots. Incidents occurring partially on a public roadway are considered to be roadway incidents.
14e3ea7b-e67c-4e74-82f1-254a11e5266e.includes: Struck by vehicle events in shoulder, medians, all parts of area designed for motorized land vehicle transportation and publicly maintained; vehicles pulling out onto public road from private drive; pedestrian crossings and bike lanes
14e3ea7b-e67c-4e74-82f1-254a11e5266e.excludes: Pedestrians struck in marked work zones (251)

b7985123-fc1b-40df-91ee-fc3ae2804174.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in roadway— unspecified
b7985123-fc1b-40df-91ee-fc3ae2804174.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by motorized land vehicles in the roadway when the detailed cause of the injury specified in codes 2521 to 2529 is unknown
b7985123-fc1b-40df-91ee-fc3ae2804174.excludes: Struck by vehicle in a work zone (251)

d091d394-43b8-42c9-8e51-31c6c8f0ecd0.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle or object propelled by another vehicle in roadway
d091d394-43b8-42c9-8e51-31c6c8f0ecd0.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by vehicles or other objects that have been propelled by a motorized land vehicle under normal operation in the public roadway.
d091d394-43b8-42c9-8e51-31c6c8f0ecd0.includes: Struck by a trash can that was hit by a truck on the road
d091d394-43b8-42c9-8e51-31c6c8f0ecd0.excludes: Struck by an object that falls from a stationary vehicle (643)

16bdda27-82c0-44d6-b84e-321420410006.title: Pedestrian struck by forward-moving vehicle in roadway
16bdda27-82c0-44d6-b84e-321420410006.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by a forward moving motorized land vehicle under normal operation in the public roadway.
16bdda27-82c0-44d6-b84e-321420410006.includes: Struck by a bus driving forward in the road
16bdda27-82c0-44d6-b84e-321420410006.excludes: struck by turning vehicles in forward motion

c8e9df3c-60bb-4546-a40c-b5d9e18fca5a.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle backing up in roadway
c8e9df3c-60bb-4546-a40c-b5d9e18fca5a.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by a motorized land vehicle backing up in the public roadway.
c8e9df3c-60bb-4546-a40c-b5d9e18fca5a.includes: Struck by a car backing up in a crosswalk

f8bfff62-d7fe-4aa6-9d17-269d73f2dd31.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in roadway— n.e.c.
f8bfff62-d7fe-4aa6-9d17-269d73f2dd31.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck in roadway areas events that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes 2520 to 2523.
f8bfff62-d7fe-4aa6-9d17-269d73f2dd31.excludes: Struck by turning vehicles in roadway (2522)

f49f3c72-4515-43d2-be75-fa4cfbb5778c.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in nonroadway area
f49f3c72-4515-43d2-be75-fa4cfbb5778c.definition: This group includes incidents occurring in all areas defined as "nonroadway": privately maintained industrial, commercial, residential, and farm premises; parking lots; and logging roads. Sidewalks and pedestrian designated areas should also be considered nonroadways unless they are intended to be shared with motorized vehicles, such as crosswalks and bike lanes. Incidents occurring partially on a public roadway are considered to be roadway incidents.
f49f3c72-4515-43d2-be75-fa4cfbb5778c.includes: Struck by vehicle incidents in industrial, commercial, residential, and farm premises; parking lots; private access roads, including for mining, logging, fire fighting, and construction; sidewalks
f49f3c72-4515-43d2-be75-fa4cfbb5778c.excludes: Struck by vehicle incidents in bike lanes that are part of publicly maintained roadway or crosswalks (252)

c84c945b-62d7-4596-8af1-51e4f60e5702.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in nonroadway area— unspecified
c84c945b-62d7-4596-8af1-51e4f60e5702.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by motorized land vehicles in nonroadway areas when the detailed cause of the injury specified in codes 2531 to 2539 is unknown
c84c945b-62d7-4596-8af1-51e4f60e5702.includes: Struck by a tractor in a field
c84c945b-62d7-4596-8af1-51e4f60e5702.excludes: Incidents in road construction zones (251); passengers of vehicles who fall and are struck (2632, 2732)

7ee75b56-7dab-4a18-ab31-973423a68668.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle or object propelled by another vehicle in nonroadway area
7ee75b56-7dab-4a18-ab31-973423a68668.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by vehicles or other objects that have been propelled by or falling from a motorized land vehicle under normal operation in a nonroadway area.
7ee75b56-7dab-4a18-ab31-973423a68668.includes: Worker struck by a cart propelled by being hit by a forklift in a warehouse
7ee75b56-7dab-4a18-ab31-973423a68668.excludes: struck by item falling from rack that was bumped by a forklift

de8d496c-5250-4baa-a70d-f6beb07b3ca1.title: Pedestrian struck by forward-moving vehicle in nonroadway area
de8d496c-5250-4baa-a70d-f6beb07b3ca1.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by a forward moving motorized land vehicle under normal operation in a nonroadway area.
de8d496c-5250-4baa-a70d-f6beb07b3ca1.includes: Struck on the runway by an airport vehicle driving forward

041a142f-19b0-42ab-a975-b7fb009599b1.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle backing up in nonroadway area
041a142f-19b0-42ab-a975-b7fb009599b1.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck by a backward moving motorized land vehicle under normal operation in a nonroadway area.
041a142f-19b0-42ab-a975-b7fb009599b1.includes: Struck on the runway by an airport vehicle backing up

c7698b86-05ba-4665-91d4-78b5c2b15525.title: Pedestrian struck by vehicle in nonroadway area— n.e.c.
c7698b86-05ba-4665-91d4-78b5c2b15525.definition: Incidents involving pedestrians struck in nonroadway areas that are known but do not fit descriptions of event codes 2531 to 2533.

4d0c2bb7-dd59-4103-99fd-a8d73f520b50.title: Pedestrian incidents involving motorized land vehicles, n.e.c.
4d0c2bb7-dd59-4103-99fd-a8d73f520b50.definition: Incidents involving injuries to pedestrians as a result of traveling motorized land vehicles or other mobile equipment that do not meet descriptions of groups 250-253.
4d0c2bb7-dd59-4103-99fd-a8d73f520b50.includes: Injuries due to near miss of pedestrian by a motor vehicle
4d0c2bb7-dd59-4103-99fd-a8d73f520b50.excludes: worker jumps out of vehicle's way.

e137592e-2758-48ec-92af-222802a919fb.title: Roadway incidents involving motorized land vehicle
e137592e-2758-48ec-92af-222802a919fb.definition: Codes in this major group apply to roadway incidents involving motorized land vehicles that injure vehicle occupants. Roadway incidents may occur on any part of publicly maintained traffic ways intended for motorized land vehicle travel, including travel lanes, shoulders, medians, and adjoining publicly maintained areas designated for vehicles (e.g. runaway truck ramp, weigh station, toll areas). It excludes private and commercial roadways, sidewalks, and parking lots. Incidents occurring partially on a public roadway are considered to be roadway incidents. Vehicle occupants include drivers/operators, passengers and persons exiting or entering vehicles or persons partially inside vehicles. The vehicles involved can be in forward or backward motion and operating under power or not.  If it cannot be determined whether a land vehicle incident occurred in a roadway or nonroadway area, code as a roadway event.

66975881-a4da-4b37-b90c-3c2a3bd26e9b.title: Roadway incidents involving motorized land vehicle— unspecified
66975881-a4da-4b37-b90c-3c2a3bd26e9b.definition: Injuries to vehicle occupants resulting from roadway incidents involving motorized land vehicles when a more detailed code from groups 261 to 269 cannot be determined.
66975881-a4da-4b37-b90c-3c2a3bd26e9b.includes: Motor vehicle incident, unspecified; 'MVA', unspecified; traffic accident
66975881-a4da-4b37-b90c-3c2a3bd26e9b.excludes: Injuries to non passengers or pedestrians (25)

8683c3b3-4fba-409a-906f-e1777dbcd84b.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)
8683c3b3-4fba-409a-906f-e1777dbcd84b.definition: Collision of a motorized land vehicle with at least one other motorized land vehicles where 1) the crash occurs  in the public roadway and 2) at least one vehicle is in motion. Code titles describe the initial position of the vehicles in relation to one another just before the crash occurred. If a vehicle contacted more than one other vehicle, code in relation to the first vehicle contacted.
8683c3b3-4fba-409a-906f-e1777dbcd84b.includes: Car with occupant rolls into another vehicle
8683c3b3-4fba-409a-906f-e1777dbcd84b.excludes: Collisions involving rail vehicles (23), collisions involving animals and non-motorized vehicles (24) roadway collisions and side of road collisions with objects other than vehicles (262); pedestrians or non passengers struck by vehicles (25)

dec652a6-d707-4ad0-a8be-f1485df093b0.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)— unspecified
dec652a6-d707-4ad0-a8be-f1485df093b0.definition: Injuries to vehicle occupants resulting from roadway collisions between motorized land vehicles when details about the initial position of the vehicles in relation to one another specified in codes 2611 to 2619 are unknown.
dec652a6-d707-4ad0-a8be-f1485df093b0.includes: Car strikes bus in the roadway
dec652a6-d707-4ad0-a8be-f1485df093b0.excludes: Car strikes animal on the side of the road (2622)

5d4c3060-4c55-4188-97e1-f54f169d5f15.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)—intersecting, turning
5d4c3060-4c55-4188-97e1-f54f169d5f15.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where injured worker's vehicle was moving through an intersection of public roadways or turning on or off a public roadway, regardless of orientation of vehicles to one another. Vehicles may be entering or exiting travel lane(s) from a private drive, side of road, or nonroadway area. The turning vehicle that of the injured worker or another driver.
5d4c3060-4c55-4188-97e1-f54f169d5f15.includes: Vehicle ran stop sign or red light; entering or exiting travel lane from private drive, parking lot, parallel parking space, shoulder or median; turning vehicles
5d4c3060-4c55-4188-97e1-f54f169d5f15.excludes: Merging/exiting from a highway entrance/exit ramps (2612)

286fa878-a440-4b61-a43d-bba4ad8fd15a.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving in same direction
286fa878-a440-4b61-a43d-bba4ad8fd15a.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where both vehicles are moving in the same direction in the roadway. Select this code if source documents make no mention of an intersection or entering/exiting the roadway.
286fa878-a440-4b61-a43d-bba4ad8fd15a.excludes: rear end collisions when both vehicles are in motion

ac6a9277-6bb8-4e49-b782-ab8bb1d0ceb4.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving in opposite directions, oncoming
ac6a9277-6bb8-4e49-b782-ab8bb1d0ceb4.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where the  vehicles are moving in opposite directions in the roadway and they collide but not in an intersection.

277e219c-1c2d-4b18-9a90-41a8f9489743.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving and standing vehicle
277e219c-1c2d-4b18-9a90-41a8f9489743.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where moving vehicle strikes a stopped vehicle either in the traffic lane or on the side of the roadway.
277e219c-1c2d-4b18-9a90-41a8f9489743.includes: Vehicles stopped in traffic or at a red light or stop sign; disabled vehicles in the roadway; roadway collision between a moving vehicle and one parked on the shoulder, side of road, or median
277e219c-1c2d-4b18-9a90-41a8f9489743.excludes: Rear end collision when both vehicles are in motion (2612)

16bef991-fc8f-4578-a76f-85d0a8550198.title: Roadway collision with other vehicle— n.e.c.
16bef991-fc8f-4578-a76f-85d0a8550198.definition: Roadway collision with other vehicle incident with  known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 2611 to 2614.
16bef991-fc8f-4578-a76f-85d0a8550198.includes: Vehicle falls from overpass, colliding with other vehicle(s)

1a6f8dbd-1e46-47f4-a1a2-173ec1ca1f40.title: Roadway collision with object other than vehicle
1a6f8dbd-1e46-47f4-a1a2-173ec1ca1f40.definition: Collisions of moving motorized land vehicles originating in public roadways with objects other than a motorized land vehicles. Code titles describe the position of the object that the vehicle struck in relation to the roadway. If the vehicle struck more than one object, select the object that was struck first.
1a6f8dbd-1e46-47f4-a1a2-173ec1ca1f40.excludes: Crashes where the worker's vehicle struck an object and then another vehicle (261); non-moving vehicle struck by object in roadway (Division 6); "collisions" with curbs, potholes, ditches (263)

c66367c5-91e0-4031-b0e7-f9c8cc61673e.title: Roadway collision with object other than vehicle— unspecified
c66367c5-91e0-4031-b0e7-f9c8cc61673e.definition: Incidents where the injured worker's vehicle strikes an object, but the position of the object relative to the roadway specified in codes 2621 to 2629 are unknown.
c66367c5-91e0-4031-b0e7-f9c8cc61673e.excludes: Collision of a vehicle with another vehicle (261)

9c6c6812-032e-481a-873b-93d7b49aa574.title: Vehicle struck by falling or flying object(s) in roadway
9c6c6812-032e-481a-873b-93d7b49aa574.definition: Moving vehicles that are struck by falling or collapsing objects in the roadway.

1a54003d-14c4-4bde-9d7e-d9db3cbc5ef8.title: Collision with moving object or animal in roadway
1a54003d-14c4-4bde-9d7e-d9db3cbc5ef8.definition: Moving vehicles that strike or are struck by moving objects or animals in a public roadway.
1a54003d-14c4-4bde-9d7e-d9db3cbc5ef8.excludes: vehicle strikes moving person in roadway

dfdf56b2-a0a1-47f1-9cbe-00c54385b5f7.title: Collision with stationary object in roadway
dfdf56b2-a0a1-47f1-9cbe-00c54385b5f7.definition: Moving vehicles that strike stationary objects in a public roadway.
dfdf56b2-a0a1-47f1-9cbe-00c54385b5f7.excludes: Vehicle strikes disabled vehicle in roadway (2614)

ffbea42e-8955-46ee-8ab1-f72bcf445d89.title: Collision with object or animal on side of roadway
ffbea42e-8955-46ee-8ab1-f72bcf445d89.definition: Moving vehicles that strike objects or animals on the side or shoulder of a public roadway, outside of the lanes of travel.
ffbea42e-8955-46ee-8ab1-f72bcf445d89.includes: Vehicle strikes guardrail or barrier on side of road
ffbea42e-8955-46ee-8ab1-f72bcf445d89.excludes: Vehicle striking building when the car started in the roadway

fac6a18a-60d4-438a-b0e1-04f8c53966f7.title: Ran off roadway and struck object— n.e.c.
fac6a18a-60d4-438a-b0e1-04f8c53966f7.definition: Moving vehicles that strike objects where the incident originated on a public roadway that are not described in codes 2621 through 2624.
fac6a18a-60d4-438a-b0e1-04f8c53966f7.includes: Vehicle falling from elevated roadway and impacting a lower level, including bodies of water; vehicle falls into sinkhole

c557e00b-1259-40e3-acf9-b0ef611969cf.title: Roadway noncollision incident
c557e00b-1259-40e3-acf9-b0ef611969cf.definition: Incidents that occur in the public roadway where there is no collision between the worker's vehicle and any other vehicle or object, but the vehicle is disabled or comes to an abrupt stop.

896c8c14-2ce9-4084-b9e5-bd8f3c34c753.title: Roadway noncollision incident— unspecified
896c8c14-2ce9-4084-b9e5-bd8f3c34c753.definition: Roadway incidents in which a collision did not occur but further details of the incident specified in codes 2631 to 2639 are unknown.

708b7382-b90f-4ab0-895f-6311663494f6.title: Roadway noncollision— vehicle overturn
708b7382-b90f-4ab0-895f-6311663494f6.definition: Incidents that occur in the public roadway where there is no collision, but the worker's vehicle overturns or rolls.
708b7382-b90f-4ab0-895f-6311663494f6.excludes: Collisions that result in a rollover or jack-knife (261-262)

28f89690-f4dc-402f-9cb0-619e892f53e7.title: Roadway noncollision— fall or jump from and struck by moving vehicle
28f89690-f4dc-402f-9cb0-619e892f53e7.definition: Falls or jumps from a moving vehicle in roadway resulting in being struck by the same vehicle or another vehicle.
28f89690-f4dc-402f-9cb0-619e892f53e7.includes: Fall from and struck by same vehicle
28f89690-f4dc-402f-9cb0-619e892f53e7.excludes: fall from and struck by another vehicle

c76fb5cb-5bb3-4705-848f-697ed28d9059.title: Roadway noncollision— fall or jump from moving vehicle
c76fb5cb-5bb3-4705-848f-697ed28d9059.definition: Falls or jumps from a moving vehicle in roadway without being struck by another vehicle
c76fb5cb-5bb3-4705-848f-697ed28d9059.excludes: Fall on or from a stationary vehicle (Division 4)

5b8395e3-3b33-4003-baa9-62fdaa536d1b.title: Roadway noncollision— fall on moving vehicle
5b8395e3-3b33-4003-baa9-62fdaa536d1b.definition: Falls, slips, and trips on moving vehicles from one part of the vehicle into cargo vats or bins or into running equipment that is part of or attached to the vehicle.
5b8395e3-3b33-4003-baa9-62fdaa536d1b.includes: Falling into tank or vat on moving truck
5b8395e3-3b33-4003-baa9-62fdaa536d1b.excludes: falling from garbage truck into trash compactor

f0be6130-ebaf-48ea-a0b5-648eb7f489ac.title: Roadway noncollision— struck by shifting, dislodged load in transport
f0be6130-ebaf-48ea-a0b5-648eb7f489ac.definition: Incidents in roadway areas when the motion of the vehicle causes the cargo it is carrying to shift or dislodge causing injury. This excludes cargo moving or shifting due to a collision.
f0be6130-ebaf-48ea-a0b5-648eb7f489ac.includes: Load comes into cab during transport
f0be6130-ebaf-48ea-a0b5-648eb7f489ac.excludes: contact with shifting load while riding in cargo area

eab3138b-385e-4119-b656-57301fb28178.title: Roadway noncollision— jack-knifed or ran off road
eab3138b-385e-4119-b656-57301fb28178.definition: Incidents where the vehicle was out of control, jack-knifes or ran off the roadway but did not overturn or collide with any object or vehicle.
eab3138b-385e-4119-b656-57301fb28178.includes: Runaway trucks; vehicle drove into a body of water without impact; incidents where vehicle ran into ditch or embankment without description of collision; trailed object comes around, makes contact with truck; trailed object detaches from pulling vehicle
eab3138b-385e-4119-b656-57301fb28178.excludes: Collisions that result in running off of the road (261-262)

280919c8-685b-48fd-b662-ed990b93208a.title: Roadway noncollision incident— n.e.c.
280919c8-685b-48fd-b662-ed990b93208a.definition: Roadway noncollision incidents with known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 2630 to 2636.
280919c8-685b-48fd-b662-ed990b93208a.includes: Injuries to unrestrained passengers when no crash occurs
280919c8-685b-48fd-b662-ed990b93208a.excludes: overexertion from prolonged sitting while driving

f0579a51-4fdc-4cc7-8675-46360e73ed58.title: Roadway incident involving motorized land vehicle— n.e.c.
f0579a51-4fdc-4cc7-8675-46360e73ed58.definition: Roadway incidents with known details that do not fit other detailed codes in major group 26. Includes incidents that don’t interrupt vehicle travel.
f0579a51-4fdc-4cc7-8675-46360e73ed58.includes: Passengers of vehicles in normal operation in roadway area
f0579a51-4fdc-4cc7-8675-46360e73ed58.excludes: injury to vehicle occupant due to hitting speed bump or pothole

faa4a69d-78bb-49c5-b716-12c5719728f1.title: Nonroadway incidents involving motorized land vehicles
faa4a69d-78bb-49c5-b716-12c5719728f1.definition: Injuries to vehicle occupants resulting from nonroadway incidents involving motorized land vehicles. Nonroadway incidents include any area that is not part of publicly maintained traffic ways intended for motorized land vehicle travel. It includes private and commercial roadways, sidewalks, parking lots, and industrial and agricultural premises. Incidents occurring partially on a public roadway are considered to be roadway incidents. Vehicle occupants include drivers/operators, passengers and persons exiting or entering vehicles or persons partially inside vehicles at the time of the incident. If it cannot be determined whether a land vehicle incident occurred in a roadway or nonroadway area, code as a roadway event.
faa4a69d-78bb-49c5-b716-12c5719728f1.includes: Industrial, commercial, residential, and farm premises; parking lots; private access roads, including for mining, logging, fire fighting, and construction; sidewalks
faa4a69d-78bb-49c5-b716-12c5719728f1.excludes: incidents in bike lanes or crosswalks that are part of publicly maintained roadway intended to motorized vehicles or crosswalks (26)

eb3128ec-f34f-4875-88da-8be05c4a7457.title: Nonroadway incident involving motorized land vehicle— unspecified
eb3128ec-f34f-4875-88da-8be05c4a7457.definition: Injuries to vehicle occupants resulting from nonroadway incidents involving motorized land vehicles when further incident details, specified in code groups 271 to 279, are unknown.

3c5f3177-0b7c-45c5-b7b2-eaf2fee94c1c.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)
3c5f3177-0b7c-45c5-b7b2-eaf2fee94c1c.definition: Collisions between two or more motorized land vehicles, not occurring on public roadways. Detailed codes describe the relative position of the vehicles to each other just before the incident occurred.
3c5f3177-0b7c-45c5-b7b2-eaf2fee94c1c.excludes: collisions involving rail vehicles (23), collisions involving animal transportation and non-motorized vehicles (24) nonroadway collisions with objects other than vehicles (272); roadway collisions (26)

999b5979-4d9e-4e76-b2d7-e6ad504606cb.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)— unspecified
