999b5979-4d9e-4e76-b2d7-e6ad504606cb.definition: Nonroadway collisions between two or more motorized land vehicles where the vehicles relative position to one another, specified in codes 2711 to 2719, was unknown.
999b5979-4d9e-4e76-b2d7-e6ad504606cb.includes: Crash of a tractor and truck at a construction site
999b5979-4d9e-4e76-b2d7-e6ad504606cb.excludes: Tractor crash with tree at a construction site (2729)

b5fe6b70-69ba-41bf-84b5-4732f077fb2b.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)—intersecting, turning
b5fe6b70-69ba-41bf-84b5-4732f077fb2b.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where injured worker's vehicle was moving through an intersection of private roadways or entering/exiting a private roadway, regardless of orientation of vehicles to one another. Also includes turning vehicles in nonroadway areas. The entering/exiting vehicle that of the injured worker or another driver.

0583c858-cdba-40a4-95db-fc59f31daaae.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving in same direction
0583c858-cdba-40a4-95db-fc59f31daaae.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where both vehicles are moving in the same direction in the nonroadway area.
0583c858-cdba-40a4-95db-fc59f31daaae.includes: Side by side crash of two vehicles driving the same way in a field

9fafe3d7-5030-4332-9de5-bbcbe4462e4b.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving in opposite directions, oncoming
9fafe3d7-5030-4332-9de5-bbcbe4462e4b.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where the vehicles are moving in opposite directions in a nonroadway area and they collide.

217ed41b-4717-41bb-abcd-6c49e53cb199.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)—moving and standing vehicle
217ed41b-4717-41bb-abcd-6c49e53cb199.definition: Collision between motorized land vehicles where one vehicle is moving in a nonroadway area and strikes a stationary vehicle.

02af3616-7e52-44f1-a55b-d8a064fff05b.title: Nonroadway collision with other vehicle(s)— n.e.c.
02af3616-7e52-44f1-a55b-d8a064fff05b.definition: Nonroadway collision incident with known details that but do not fit descriptions of event codes 2710 to 2714.

3374dc38-38af-424c-96de-578f3bc3da62.title: Nonroadway collision with object other than vehicle
3374dc38-38af-424c-96de-578f3bc3da62.definition: Nonroadway collisions with objects other than vehicles and mobile equipment.

94abadf2-cf42-42ac-ac73-fc569aa2cea3.title: Nonroadway collision with object or animal in path of travel— unspecified
94abadf2-cf42-42ac-ac73-fc569aa2cea3.definition: Nonroadway collisions with objects other than motorized land vehicles and mobile equipment when information about how the objects came into contact with the vehicle, specified in codes 2721 to 2729, is unknown.

20a17b53-5154-4898-b254-53000a9ccd31.title: Vehicle struck by falling or flying object(s), nonroadway
20a17b53-5154-4898-b254-53000a9ccd31.definition: Moving vehicles or mobile equipment that are struck by falling or collapsing objects in nonroadway or private roadway areas.

33bf3cfc-81cb-419a-83ff-441ec82091c7.title: Collision with moving object or animal, nonroadway
33bf3cfc-81cb-419a-83ff-441ec82091c7.definition: Moving vehicles or mobile equipment that strike or are struck by moving objects or animals while driving, operating in nonroadway areas.
33bf3cfc-81cb-419a-83ff-441ec82091c7.excludes: vehicle strikes moving person in nonroadway

f4c9ee9a-4782-49fc-ab2f-4a2fa6b72340.title: Collision with stationary object, nonroadway
f4c9ee9a-4782-49fc-ab2f-4a2fa6b72340.definition: Moving vehicles or mobile equipment that strike stationary objects while driving, operating in nonroadway areas.
f4c9ee9a-4782-49fc-ab2f-4a2fa6b72340.excludes: Vehicle strikes disabled vehicle in roadway (2614)

9d234c3f-8d09-4a86-b45f-982bb737f599.title: Nonroadway collision with object or animal — n.e.c.
9d234c3f-8d09-4a86-b45f-982bb737f599.definition: Moving vehicles that strike objects where the incident occurred on a private roadway or nonroadway area that are not described in codes 2721 through 2723.
9d234c3f-8d09-4a86-b45f-982bb737f599.includes: Vehicle struck a shed at construction site

932ab415-9688-4674-ba28-50641254a9c2.title: Nonroadway noncollision incident
932ab415-9688-4674-ba28-50641254a9c2.definition: Incidents where injured worker's vehicle does not collide with any other vehicle or object.

2534b7f8-dc61-438c-aa68-d2aef4c26e64.title: Nonroadway noncollision incident— unspecified
2534b7f8-dc61-438c-aa68-d2aef4c26e64.definition: Nonroadway incidents in which a collision did not occur but further details of the incident, specified in codes 2731 to 2739, are unknown.
2534b7f8-dc61-438c-aa68-d2aef4c26e64.excludes: Falls occurring on moving vehicles in roadway (2634)

a2a17180-6540-453e-a3e9-7f0facabee8e.title: Nonroadway noncollision— vehicle overturn
a2a17180-6540-453e-a3e9-7f0facabee8e.definition: Incidents that occur in a nonroadway area where there is no collision, but the worker's vehicle overturns or rolls.
a2a17180-6540-453e-a3e9-7f0facabee8e.excludes: Jack-knife in a nonroadway area as a result of a collision (271-272)

c092113a-c848-4efe-9b3a-043e65e40b88.title: Nonroadway noncollision— fall or jump from and struck by moving vehicle
c092113a-c848-4efe-9b3a-043e65e40b88.definition: Falls or jumps from a vehicle in non roadway areas not due to a collision or jack knife that result in being struck by that same vehicle or another vehicle. Worker may be partially or totally onboard the vehicle when the fall occurs.
c092113a-c848-4efe-9b3a-043e65e40b88.includes: Fall from and struck by same vehicle
c092113a-c848-4efe-9b3a-043e65e40b88.excludes: fall from and struck by another vehicle

aed009a1-c90c-4679-af67-17abce5ab896.title: Nonroadway noncollision— fall or jump from moving vehicle
aed009a1-c90c-4679-af67-17abce5ab896.definition: Falls or jumps from a vehicle in nonroadway areas not due to a collision or jack knife. Worker may be partially or totally onboard the vehicle when the fall occurs.
aed009a1-c90c-4679-af67-17abce5ab896.includes: Fall while attempting to board a rolling vehicle
aed009a1-c90c-4679-af67-17abce5ab896.excludes: falls or jumps from a vehicle not due to a collision or jack knife

8773d39f-78c9-4726-8147-2a07da598dc5.title: Nonroadway noncollision— fall on moving vehicle
8773d39f-78c9-4726-8147-2a07da598dc5.definition: Falls on moving vehicles in nonroadway areas, not due to a collision or jack knife, from one part of the vehicle into cargo vats or bins or into running equipment that is part of or attached to the vehicle.
8773d39f-78c9-4726-8147-2a07da598dc5.includes: Falling into tank or vat on moving truck
8773d39f-78c9-4726-8147-2a07da598dc5.excludes: fall on moving farm equipment into running machinery

16e9e877-e0a3-433c-9ac3-19d3d235391a.title: Nonroadway noncollision— Struck by shifting, dislodged load in transport
16e9e877-e0a3-433c-9ac3-19d3d235391a.definition: Incidents in nonroadway areas when the motion of the vehicle causes the cargo it is carrying to shift or dislodge causing injury. This excludes cargo moving or shifting due to a collision
16e9e877-e0a3-433c-9ac3-19d3d235391a.includes: Vehicle cab struck while pulling out stump
16e9e877-e0a3-433c-9ac3-19d3d235391a.excludes: cargo coming through back window of a truck cab

9b6e6bba-55b4-434c-a55f-4bb40b851aef.title: Nonroadway noncollision— jack-knifed or ran off driving surface
9b6e6bba-55b4-434c-a55f-4bb40b851aef.definition: Incidents that occur in a nonroadway area where the vehicle was out of control, jack-knifes or ran off the driving surface but did not overturn or collide with any object or vehicle.
9b6e6bba-55b4-434c-a55f-4bb40b851aef.includes: Tractor drives or rolls into a lake from a field
9b6e6bba-55b4-434c-a55f-4bb40b851aef.excludes: ran off driving surface and jack knifed

f26b42f9-8642-40ce-9624-da57ac559ac0.title: Nonroadway noncollision incident— n.e.c.
f26b42f9-8642-40ce-9624-da57ac559ac0.definition: Nonroadway noncollision incidents with known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 2730 to 2736.
f26b42f9-8642-40ce-9624-da57ac559ac0.includes: Jarring or vibration onboard vehicle without other incident

4898a998-2056-4e13-98de-626e58dd3e7f.title: Nonroadway incident involving motorized land vehicle— n.e.c.
4898a998-2056-4e13-98de-626e58dd3e7f.definition: Nonroadway incidents with known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 2710 to 2739.
4898a998-2056-4e13-98de-626e58dd3e7f.includes: Injured passengers of vehicles in non-normal operation in nonroadway area

6b34d329-11a0-4fa7-a6a2-934064adf4dc.title: Transportation incidents— n.e.c.
6b34d329-11a0-4fa7-a6a2-934064adf4dc.definition: Transportation incidents with known details that do not fit descriptions of any event codes in codes 20 through 279.

e0a391f8-2e71-40c5-925a-474987e7dd48.title: EXPLOSIONS AND FIRES
e0a391f8-2e71-40c5-925a-474987e7dd48.definition: Codes in this division include any type of injury or illness resulting from explosions or active fires.
e0a391f8-2e71-40c5-925a-474987e7dd48.excludes: Bombing, arson (1115); fires resulting from transportation incidents (Division 2); contact with a controlled heat source or hot objects or substances (533), unless the person's clothes catch fire (326).  Injuries resulting from unsafe conditions (i.e. building collapse) after the fire has been extinguished should be coded in the appropriate non-fire event; smoke inhalation where no fire or explosion was present (553)

071b5755-1719-4163-81e0-1c1ea03d06b3.title: Explosions and fires— unspecified
071b5755-1719-4163-81e0-1c1ea03d06b3.definition: Events involving combustion of materials where it cannot be determined whether there was an explosion component.

f4fa4477-9c61-42cf-b9f9-a54f031f86da.title: Explosions
f4fa4477-9c61-42cf-b9f9-a54f031f86da.definition: Codes in this major group apply to cases in which the injury or illness resulted from an explosion. An explosion is a rapid expansion, outbreak, bursting, or upheaval.  Explosions resulting from fires should also be coded as explosions, regardless of whether the fire occurred first. Codes apply to explosions of all sizes as well as unintentional and intentionally-set explosions.
f4fa4477-9c61-42cf-b9f9-a54f031f86da.includes: Chemical explosions; pressure (mechanical) explosions; nuclear explosions; explosions, such as backdrafts, that occur due to an established fire
f4fa4477-9c61-42cf-b9f9-a54f031f86da.excludes: Intentional bombing (1115); explosions on vehicles in transportation operations (Division 2); collapse due to structural integrity (63); arc explosions, arc blasts (513)

3da44fa8-8ca2-46ee-b627-4ea93317c176.title: Explosion— unspecified
3da44fa8-8ca2-46ee-b627-4ea93317c176.definition: Explosions where a more specific code from 311 to 314 cannot be determined.

b7e20e1a-f2ec-488f-b0de-ab75fc683deb.title: Intentionally set explosion
b7e20e1a-f2ec-488f-b0de-ab75fc683deb.definition: Events resulting from the intentional detonation of explosives, except as a violent act with intent to harm. Includes explosives that detonate on purpose or by accident

54b8e2e3-c27b-4eaf-91e8-bf29bf76d95d.title: Dust explosion
54b8e2e3-c27b-4eaf-91e8-bf29bf76d95d.definition: Rapid combustion of fine particles suspended in the air within an enclosed location.

40a0b5c7-04f3-4303-baec-8d608080c654.title: Explosion of pressure vessel, piping, or tire
40a0b5c7-04f3-4303-baec-8d608080c654.definition: Rapid combustion or release of pressure of vapors, gases or liquids within a pressurized container.
40a0b5c7-04f3-4303-baec-8d608080c654.includes: Explosions of aerosol cans, automobile tires, steam vessels, pipes, hoses, valves, pump explosion
40a0b5c7-04f3-4303-baec-8d608080c654.excludes: Struck by discharged or flying object or substance (642)

98d72586-87eb-4454-b3ba-66d42d9d0ba0.title: Explosion of nonpressurized vapors, gases, or liquids
98d72586-87eb-4454-b3ba-66d42d9d0ba0.definition: Rapid combustion of vapors, gases or liquids within a nonpressurized container or in the atmosphere.

5729ab13-48d0-4d4c-af4b-8646803817d2.title: Explosion— n.e.c.
5729ab13-48d0-4d4c-af4b-8646803817d2.definition: Explosions with known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 310 to 314.

41ab597c-0bfa-4c55-b7fb-345c59c1a14d.title: Fires (without explosions)
41ab597c-0bfa-4c55-b7fb-345c59c1a14d.definition: Codes in this major group apply to cases in which the injury or illness resulted from exposure to an active fire or as a result of fighting a fire. Generally, if the worker was considered to be at the scene of an active fire, a code from Event 3 would be selected over other event codes, even if the worker experienced a fall, exposure, or contact incident at the scene of a fire.  If an explosion occurred at any point during a fire, code as an explosion.
41ab597c-0bfa-4c55-b7fb-345c59c1a14d.includes: forest or wildfires; structural fires with or without collapse; vehicle or machinery fires, except during transport; small scale fires
41ab597c-0bfa-4c55-b7fb-345c59c1a14d.excludes: Fires that result from or produce an explosion (31); Incidents occurring as a result of a fire that is no longer active, such as collapse of a damaged building.

7ac8fa46-8976-405d-8963-1dc0c73d5440.title: Fire— unspecified
7ac8fa46-8976-405d-8963-1dc0c73d5440.definition: Fires without explosions when the type or extent of the fire is unknown specified in codes 321 to 329 cannot be determined.

166e1df8-d1f6-4644-97be-01c0ce8d674a.title: Forest fire or wildfire
166e1df8-d1f6-4644-97be-01c0ce8d674a.definition: Large scale fires that spread over woodland or brush. They may burn over long durations of several days to several weeks. Forest fires or wildfires causing a structure or other object to catch fire are coded here.
166e1df8-d1f6-4644-97be-01c0ce8d674a.includes: Structural and building fires caused by wildfires

a1ec48d6-2d0c-4f71-abce-d0036d23f1ac.title: Structural fire with collapse
a1ec48d6-2d0c-4f71-abce-d0036d23f1ac.definition: Fires without an explosion that result in a collapsing building, structure, or structural element during fire. Small scale fires that spread to become a structural fire are coded here.
a1ec48d6-2d0c-4f71-abce-d0036d23f1ac.includes: Fires resulting in partial or full roof collapse

2f98b0fa-6938-4d0f-b157-1d9eb7df300b.title: Structural fire without collapse
2f98b0fa-6938-4d0f-b157-1d9eb7df300b.definition: Fires without an explosion involving parts of building, structure, or structural element without collapse of structure. Select this code when the fire was known to be structural, but details about collapse are unknown.
2f98b0fa-6938-4d0f-b157-1d9eb7df300b.includes: Vehicular (non-transport) or machinery fires and small scale fires that spread to surrounding structures, but do not involve structural collapse.
2f98b0fa-6938-4d0f-b157-1d9eb7df300b.excludes: Forest and wildfires that spread to structures (321)

c424c47b-659f-4c83-bdc1-5c7a977d9589.title: Vehicle or machinery fire
c424c47b-659f-4c83-bdc1-5c7a977d9589.definition: Fires without an explosion occurring to machinery (whether running or turned off) and vehicles not engaged in transportation operations. If a transportation incident precedes the fire, select event from Division 2.
c424c47b-659f-4c83-bdc1-5c7a977d9589.includes: Fire-related injuries to non-passengers responding to vehicle or machinery fire

e17dd8d1-a2fd-4c66-a08f-1ee8eb926f2c.title: Fire— small-scale, limited
e17dd8d1-a2fd-4c66-a08f-1ee8eb926f2c.definition: Steadily burning fires either indoors or outdoors which are contained to a limited area and do not spread to the surrounding environment or structures. May occur in a designated area for burning such as a fireplace or a firepit, or an unintentional fire which does not ignite other nearby materials.
e17dd8d1-a2fd-4c66-a08f-1ee8eb926f2c.includes: Brush or vegetation fires that do not spread to surrounding areas

f031613b-cc25-490d-891f-ed9908983e1a.title: Ignition of clothing
f031613b-cc25-490d-891f-ed9908983e1a.definition: Instances where an object worn on the person of a worker ignites without the occurrence of a larger fire. This may be caused by sparks or exposure to a controlled source of heat or flame.
f031613b-cc25-490d-891f-ed9908983e1a.includes: ignition of hair; ignition of worn accessories (i.e. backpack, purse); ignition due to flying sparks without other fire; ignition from intentional, controlled flames in normal operation and heat sources i.e. stoves, radiators, furnaces, kilns, etc.; ignition from small scale, intentional fires, e.g. bonfires or campfires;
f031613b-cc25-490d-891f-ed9908983e1a.excludes: ignition of clothing from non-controlled fire; contact burns and radiant burns without ignition of clothing or person from a controlled heat source (i.e. touching a burner, hot oil splash) (Division 5); Heat-exhaustion or related conditions from ambient radiating heat (i.e. working in boiler room) (Division 5)

c9773725-1572-43de-a7f0-626cd9caa792.title: Flash fire
c9773725-1572-43de-a7f0-626cd9caa792.definition: Short-duration fire that spreads rapidly by means of a flame front through a diffuse fuel, such as dust or ignitable vapors, without the production of damaging pressure (as in an explosion). These types of fires self-extinguish from burning all available fuel as opposed to requiring intervention to put out, and are typically less than 3 seconds in duration.
c9773725-1572-43de-a7f0-626cd9caa792.includes: Fire ball that dissipates; ignition of vapors, gases or liquids without description of an explosion
c9773725-1572-43de-a7f0-626cd9caa792.excludes: Flashover occurring in structural fire (322 or 323)

7a23bd41-9b2e-412f-82de-60efc01fbd65.title: Nonstructural fire— n.e.c.
7a23bd41-9b2e-412f-82de-60efc01fbd65.definition: Fires without explosions with known details that do not fit descriptions of event codes 320-327.

995a16fa-d0f0-4d05-a698-b593060dc293.title: FALLS, SLIPS, TRIPS
995a16fa-d0f0-4d05-a698-b593060dc293.definition: Codes in this division apply to falls and jumps to lower levels, falls on the same level, and slips, trips, and stumbles that do not result in a fall. Jumps are coded the same as falls unless self-harm was intended.  The division also includes other nontransport-related falls resulting in drowning or other nonimpact injuries. The order of precedence is reflected in the order of codes. Injuries due to trying to catch oneself to prevent a fall are coded as falls as is impact with a surface or object due to a slip, trip, or loss of balance.
995a16fa-d0f0-4d05-a698-b593060dc293.includes: Falls, jumps, slips, trips, stumbles, falls into water resulting in drowning; falls on or from vehicles not in transport;  slips, trips, or stumbles without falling; falls and jumps that were curtailed by a personal arrest device
995a16fa-d0f0-4d05-a698-b593060dc293.excludes: Falls due to violence (Division 1), falls on vehicles during transport (Division 2), falls or jumps as a result of fires or explosions (Division 3); parachute jumps (215); injury due to stepping to a lower level (such as, off a ladder, out of a vehicle, or off a curb) with no indication of forcible contact from a fall (such as a fracture or a bruise) (73)

844402c1-bfce-4f26-851c-a9f74d966cab.title: Fall, slip, trip— unspecified
844402c1-bfce-4f26-851c-a9f74d966cab.definition: Incidents where a worker was known to have slipped, tripped, or fallen, but it cannot be determined which of these events occurred.

56d9ac48-a4a4-4dca-97c3-44da5585cdb1.title: Fall to lower level
56d9ac48-a4a4-4dca-97c3-44da5585cdb1.definition: Codes in this major group include falls and jumps to a lower level in which the injury was produced by impact between the injured person and a surface or object, where the motion of the person and the force of impact were generated by gravity, and the point of contact with the surface or object was lower than the surface supporting the person at the start of the fall.  Falls from ground level to a lower level, such as into storm drains or sewers, are coded here. Falls resulting from or causing another harmful event, such as chemical exposure,  electric shock or a contact injury where significant injuries result from both the fall and the other event are also included here. Fall height is measure as the difference between the surface from which the decedent fell to the surface on which they landed. Most falls of one or two stories will be coded as falls from 6 through 30 feet; falls of three or more stories will be coded as falls of more than 30 feet. Distances should be rounded to the nearest foot. Falls curtailed by fall arrest systems should be selected only if the equipment curtailed the fall but caused an injury. If a fall arrest system is not mentioned in source documents, or if it failed and the worker struck the ground, code the height of the fall as usual.
56d9ac48-a4a4-4dca-97c3-44da5585cdb1.includes: Jumps to lower level, falls from any structure or object, (including ladders, scaffolds, trees, roof tops, etc.); falls into water resulting in drowning; falls to lower level resulting from contact or exposure to a harmful substance when the fall contributes to the injury
56d9ac48-a4a4-4dca-97c3-44da5585cdb1.excludes: Stepping to a lower level without indication of forcible contact (Division 7);  falls resulting from violent incidents (Division 1), transportation incidents (Division 2), or fires or explosions (Division 3)

3e2570ec-2e82-44e1-95b1-85a92234131a.title: Fall to lower level— unspecified
3e2570ec-2e82-44e1-95b1-85a92234131a.definition: Fall or jump to a lower level where the fall is known to have produced an injury, but type of fall detailed in codes 411-419 cannot be determined.

df59a70c-6b1d-42af-b0c4-f8840b3d54df.title: Fall to lower level from collapsing structure or equipment
df59a70c-6b1d-42af-b0c4-f8840b3d54df.definition: Falls to a lower level due to a collapse of structures or machinery, such as manlifts or cranes.
df59a70c-6b1d-42af-b0c4-f8840b3d54df.includes: Fall from ladder tipping over or collapsing
df59a70c-6b1d-42af-b0c4-f8840b3d54df.excludes: fall from tipping or collapsing boom truck or manlift

efc32768-3303-4819-adbb-986dacf76260.title: Fall to lower level from collapsing structure or equipment— unspecified
efc32768-3303-4819-adbb-986dacf76260.definition: Falls to a lower level due to a collapse of structures or machinery, such as manlifts or cranes when the distance of the fall is unknown.

3f28d5cb-c0d0-40cf-a9aa-ae376b5ed7e9.title: Fall to lower level from collapsing structure or equipment— less than 6 feet
3f28d5cb-c0d0-40cf-a9aa-ae376b5ed7e9.definition: Falls to a lower level due to a collapse of structures or machinery, such as manlifts or cranes when the distance is less than 6 feet.
3f28d5cb-c0d0-40cf-a9aa-ae376b5ed7e9.includes: Fall from a chair, step stool or table collapsing

737c67f8-ead0-421b-a51c-39f5f69c2d97.title: Fall to lower level from collapsing structure or equipment— 6 to 30 feet
737c67f8-ead0-421b-a51c-39f5f69c2d97.definition: Falls to a lower level due to a collapse of structures or machinery, such as manlifts or cranes when the distance of the fall is 6 through 30 feet.
737c67f8-ead0-421b-a51c-39f5f69c2d97.includes: Falls described as one or two stories without providing a numerical distance

f7a3ed0f-e5c7-45d0-963f-ce9debe240c8.title: Fall to lower level from collapsing structure or equipment— more than 30 feet
f7a3ed0f-e5c7-45d0-963f-ce9debe240c8.definition: Falls to a lower level due to a collapse of structures or machinery, such as manlifts or cranes when the distance of the fall over 30 feet.
f7a3ed0f-e5c7-45d0-963f-ce9debe240c8.includes: Falls described as three or more stories without a different height specified without providing a numerical distance

1deacee6-4230-4aed-81f6-fd1ac1088546.title: Fall to lower level resulting from exposure or contact
1deacee6-4230-4aed-81f6-fd1ac1088546.definition: Falls to lower level that were initiated by contact between the worker and another object.
1deacee6-4230-4aed-81f6-fd1ac1088546.includes: Struck by hand tool resulting in loss of balance and fall from ladder
1deacee6-4230-4aed-81f6-fd1ac1088546.excludes: worker bumped by 2x4 lumber and falls off roof

5ab6d41e-50c4-4a5b-b760-730655cf2ba9.title: Fall to lower level resulting from exposure or contact— unspecified
5ab6d41e-50c4-4a5b-b760-730655cf2ba9.definition: Falls to lower level that were initiated by contact between the worker and another object and the distance of the fall is unknown.
5ab6d41e-50c4-4a5b-b760-730655cf2ba9.excludes: Transportation incidents that result in a fall (Division 2)

b8b3ce7c-14eb-4020-8405-11f282527879.title: Fall to lower level resulting from exposure or contact— less than 6 feet
b8b3ce7c-14eb-4020-8405-11f282527879.definition: Falls to lower level that were initiated by contact between the worker and another object where the distance of the fall is less than 6 ft.
b8b3ce7c-14eb-4020-8405-11f282527879.excludes: Transportation incidents that result in a fall (Division 2)

ef6e274a-6212-46a9-898c-a6e7dfe1efcc.title: Fall to lower level resulting from exposure or contact— 6 to 30 feet
ef6e274a-6212-46a9-898c-a6e7dfe1efcc.definition: Falls to lower level that were initiated by contact between the worker and another object where the distance of the fall is 6 through 30 ft.
ef6e274a-6212-46a9-898c-a6e7dfe1efcc.includes: Falls described as one or two stories without a different height specified
ef6e274a-6212-46a9-898c-a6e7dfe1efcc.excludes: Transportation incidents that result in a fall (Division 2)

c53d5e84-01d7-4fb0-8ca8-cbe45806d7e0.title: Fall to lower level resulting from exposure or contact— more than 30 feet
c53d5e84-01d7-4fb0-8ca8-cbe45806d7e0.definition: Falls to lower level that were initiated by contact between the worker and another object where the distance of the fall is greater than 30 ft.
c53d5e84-01d7-4fb0-8ca8-cbe45806d7e0.includes: Falls described as three or more stories without a different height specified
c53d5e84-01d7-4fb0-8ca8-cbe45806d7e0.excludes: Transportation incidents that result in a fall (Division 2)

f8620311-e705-426c-bad8-d4d42e092550.title: Fall to lower level resulting in exposure or contact
f8620311-e705-426c-bad8-d4d42e092550.definition: Falls to lower level where the worker fell onto or into an object or substance that produces injuries beyond those that resulted from the fall.  This code is typically reserved for cases when a minor fall results in contact or exposure with objects or substances that were independently harmful and excludes falls onto objects or structures where the force of the fall was the primary cause of injury.
f8620311-e705-426c-bad8-d4d42e092550.includes: Fall onto running machinery, fall into harmful substance such as a hot liquid or caustic chemical

2fa73089-bacf-4792-8276-6a41464911ef.title: Fall to lower level resulting in exposure or contact— unspecified
2fa73089-bacf-4792-8276-6a41464911ef.definition: Falls to lower level where the worker fell onto or into an object or substance that contributes to the injuries beyond the injuries resulting from the fall and the distance of the fall is unknown.

888494d4-ccb0-4649-af5c-bcdb3bd84c04.title: Fall to lower level resulting in exposure or contact— less than 6 feet
888494d4-ccb0-4649-af5c-bcdb3bd84c04.definition: Falls to lower level where the worker fell onto or into an object or substance that contributes to the injuries beyond the injuries resulting from the fall and the distance of the fall is less than 6 ft.

83a96a5c-a37c-4dd0-b1b2-ef4ccbe6ef6e.title: Fall to lower level resulting in exposure or contact— 6 to 30 feet
83a96a5c-a37c-4dd0-b1b2-ef4ccbe6ef6e.definition: Falls to lower level where the worker fell onto or into an object or substance that contributes to the injuries beyond the injuries resulting from the fall and the distance of the fall is 6 through 30 ft.
83a96a5c-a37c-4dd0-b1b2-ef4ccbe6ef6e.includes: Falls described as one or two stories without a different height specified

dc16d050-be6f-43ce-8264-467817f5bf44.title: Fall to lower level resulting in exposure or contact— more than 30 feet
dc16d050-be6f-43ce-8264-467817f5bf44.definition: Falls to lower level where the worker fell onto or into an object or substance that contributes to the injuries beyond the injuries resulting from the fall and the distance of the fall is over 30 ft.
dc16d050-be6f-43ce-8264-467817f5bf44.includes: Falls described as three or more stories without a different height specified

4a0bf61f-0f8e-456f-956f-0b956b150187.title: Other fall to lower level
4a0bf61f-0f8e-456f-956f-0b956b150187.definition: Falls to lower level other than falls resulting from exposure to harmful substance or environment, falls from a collapsing structure or equipment,  falls resulting from contact with object or equipment, or falls resulting in exposure or contact.
4a0bf61f-0f8e-456f-956f-0b956b150187.includes: Falls through existing openings (e.g. roof opening or skylights); falls that occur while the worker is standing on an object, such as a chair; falls onto or against structures or structural elements; falls onto or against sharp objects; falls down stairs; falls due to irregular elevator movement, except freefall drop (639)
4a0bf61f-0f8e-456f-956f-0b956b150187.excludes: Falls curtailed by fall arrest systems (419)

4e6252ca-95c7-4d94-bd92-45cf02d8b935.title: Other fall to lower level— unspecified
4e6252ca-95c7-4d94-bd92-45cf02d8b935.definition: Falls to lower level other than falls resulting from exposure to harmful substance or environment, falls from a collapsing structure or equipment,  falls resulting from contact with object or equipment, or falls resulting in exposure or contact, when the distance of the fall is unknown.

b43c2f17-d815-482a-aea0-ab60864eae26.title: Other fall to lower level— less than 6 feet
b43c2f17-d815-482a-aea0-ab60864eae26.definition: Falls to lower level of less than 6 feet other than those resulting from exposure to harmful substance or environment, falls from a collapsing structure or equipment, falls resulting from contact with object or equipment, falls resulting in exposure or contact,  or when the full impact of the fall is broken by a personal fall arrest system.
b43c2f17-d815-482a-aea0-ab60864eae26.includes: Fall into pool or body of water from ground level
b43c2f17-d815-482a-aea0-ab60864eae26.excludes: fall out of a truck trailer

c6268c46-8dc2-4e5a-bd52-ddd5bafd6289.title: Other fall to lower level— 6 to 30 feet
c6268c46-8dc2-4e5a-bd52-ddd5bafd6289.definition: Falls to lower level of 6 through 30 feet other than those resulting from exposure to harmful substance or environment, falls from a collapsing structure or equipment,  falls resulting from contact with object or equipment, falls resulting in exposure or contact,  or when the full impact of the fall is broken by a personal fall arrest system.
c6268c46-8dc2-4e5a-bd52-ddd5bafd6289.includes: Falls described as one or two stories without a different height specified

a3143f22-e20d-4ecd-b6f4-1ae3c53c2925.title: Other fall to lower level— more than 30 feet
a3143f22-e20d-4ecd-b6f4-1ae3c53c2925.definition: Falls to lower level of greater than 30 feet other than those resulting from exposure to harmful substance or environment, falls from a collapsing structure or equipment, falls resulting from contact with object or equipment, falls resulting in exposure or contact,  or when the full impact of the fall is broken by a personal fall arrest system.
a3143f22-e20d-4ecd-b6f4-1ae3c53c2925.includes: Falls described as three or more stories without a different height specified

7f422ff2-8b81-4453-bd5b-342afb34087a.title: Fall to lower level— caught self or curtailed
7f422ff2-8b81-4453-bd5b-342afb34087a.definition: Falls to lower level where, regardless of cause, where the full impact of the fall was prevented by catching oneself or a personal fall arrest system.
7f422ff2-8b81-4453-bd5b-342afb34087a.includes: Fall and catch oneself, caught by fall net, caught by personal fall arrest system
7f422ff2-8b81-4453-bd5b-342afb34087a.excludes: Fall arrest system worn, but failed to prevent fall (e.g. not tied off properly) (41)

ad123603-2f35-4ce4-881c-488e5e60e253.title: Slip, trip, stumble while stepping between levels
ad123603-2f35-4ce4-881c-488e5e60e253.definition: Slips, trips or stumbles while the injured worker is stepping from one surface to another surface that is either higher or lower. This code is applicable when it is unknown what level the worker landed on or when it is unknown if a fall occurred. If a fall to lower level was known to occur, select appropriate code in Event group 41, Fall to lower level.
ad123603-2f35-4ce4-881c-488e5e60e253.includes: "Missed step"; fall "on" or "up" stairs when fall to lower level is unknown; tripping or falling over curbs, slips and stumbles while boarding or alighting vehicles

bf6da548-98fe-4645-a9f1-08230e924fa5.title: Slip, trip, stumble or fall on same level
bf6da548-98fe-4645-a9f1-08230e924fa5.definition: Fall on same level and slip, trip without fall

4e2ed37d-5a6c-4141-b3f4-d5b2650eb041.title: Slip, trip, stumble or fall on same level— fall unspecified
4e2ed37d-5a6c-4141-b3f4-d5b2650eb041.definition: Select this code when it cannot be determined whether the injured worker fell or not.

e69458fe-5803-4b6e-b5e2-5c517b4a4871.title: Fall on same level
e69458fe-5803-4b6e-b5e2-5c517b4a4871.definition: Instances in which the injury was produced by impact between the injured person and another surface without elevation, where the motion of the person was generated by gravity following the individual’s loss of equilibrium and, the point of contact with the source of injury was at the same level or above the surface supporting the person at the inception of the fall. Nonfatal falls are coded here if there is no indication that the worker was at an elevation at the inception of the fall. Falls to the ground after being incapacitated by another event (e.g. struck by falling object) should be coded to reflect that precipitating harmful event.
e69458fe-5803-4b6e-b5e2-5c517b4a4871.includes: Fall from chair while sitting; person unable to maintain upright position; falls due to standing on moving surfaces, such as moving walkways or elevators; leg goes through floor or into a hole without falling to lower level

479fa645-431a-4092-9e13-5a0b5a164daf.title: Fall on same level— unspecified
479fa645-431a-4092-9e13-5a0b5a164daf.definition: Falls on the same level  when a more specific code from 4311 to 4319 cannot be determined.

83965d3a-d292-46cf-aefd-cb10aceee104.title: Fall on same level resulting in exposure or contact
83965d3a-d292-46cf-aefd-cb10aceee104.definition: Falls on the same level where the worker fell onto or against an object or into a substance that contributed to the injuries, whether by impact or additional injuries related to exposure or contact.
83965d3a-d292-46cf-aefd-cb10aceee104.includes: Fall on same level into running machine

ecfb8c24-a8e2-4fc7-8757-dec2513f2216.title: Fall on same level due to slip or trip
ecfb8c24-a8e2-4fc7-8757-dec2513f2216.definition: Falls on the same level resulting from slipping on a surface or substance or tripping over an object or surface irregularity. Falls on stairs or curbs on the same level are considered to be tripping over a surface irregularity.
ecfb8c24-a8e2-4fc7-8757-dec2513f2216.includes: Fall from stepping in a hole

4ecdf5f2-8131-4bc0-a594-8021733b42e6.title: Fall while sitting
4ecdf5f2-8131-4bc0-a594-8021733b42e6.definition: Falls from an object used to sit, when the worker is in a seated position, onto a surface that is on the same level as the object.
4ecdf5f2-8131-4bc0-a594-8021733b42e6.includes: Fall from chair or stool; fall while sitting, fall while attempting to sit, fall while getting up from sitting

5896e303-0740-40c5-8921-b481e9e9b0b2.title: Fall on same level and catch oneself
5896e303-0740-40c5-8921-b481e9e9b0b2.definition: Injuries resulting from efforts to catch oneself after a fall has been initiated, but do not include completed falls (i.e. hitting the ground) or falling against object or surface.
5896e303-0740-40c5-8921-b481e9e9b0b2.includes: Grabbing a railing to prevent fall
5896e303-0740-40c5-8921-b481e9e9b0b2.excludes: another person catches falling worker and prevents fall

c316a741-76b5-477a-bfd4-0605d6955abe.title: Fall on same level— n.e.c.
c316a741-76b5-477a-bfd4-0605d6955abe.definition: Falls that are not the result of tripping or slipping.
c316a741-76b5-477a-bfd4-0605d6955abe.excludes: Fall as a result of slip or trip (4312)

2dfce417-cf37-449e-ad32-3b81bd913ecd.title: Slip, trip, stumble on same level— without fall
2dfce417-cf37-449e-ad32-3b81bd913ecd.definition: Slips, trips, missteps or stumbles without a fall or inadvertent contact with an object or surface. Slips, trips, and stumbles resulting in falls are coded in 41 (lower level) or 43 (same level).
2dfce417-cf37-449e-ad32-3b81bd913ecd.excludes: tripped over oneself or an object without fall

8e76dbf9-cdf5-4c15-85bf-ee9d0139a122.title: Fall, slip, trip— n.e.c.
8e76dbf9-cdf5-4c15-85bf-ee9d0139a122.definition: Falls, slips or trips where the event is known but does not fit descriptions of event groups 41 to 43.

bcb4b933-9749-4cc8-b2cc-1bbff04ee0af.title: EXPOSURE TO HARMFUL SUBSTANCES, ENVIRONMENTS
bcb4b933-9749-4cc8-b2cc-1bbff04ee0af.definition: Codes in this division apply to injuries that are the result of an exposure to a condition or substance in the work environment.
bcb4b933-9749-4cc8-b2cc-1bbff04ee0af.includes: Exposure to electricity, hot and cold environments or objects, caustic or poisonous substances or oxygen deficiency; drug overdoses
bcb4b933-9749-4cc8-b2cc-1bbff04ee0af.excludes: Exposures resulting from violence and other injuries by persons (Division 1), transportation incidents (Division 3) , and fires or explosions (Division 3); drug overdoses from intentional self harm (125)

cc535317-dbcb-4320-a723-b41dd6bcb966.title: Exposure to harmful substances, environments— unspecified
cc535317-dbcb-4320-a723-b41dd6bcb966.definition: Exposures to harmful substances or environments when no information about the type of workplace exposure is known.
cc535317-dbcb-4320-a723-b41dd6bcb966.includes: Reactions like allergies, rashes, hives, etc. that stem from exposure in the workplace but cannot be linked back to a specific substance or environment.

28db9440-76a1-43b0-8236-5ede2a8faaf8.title: Exposure to electricity
28db9440-76a1-43b0-8236-5ede2a8faaf8.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are a result of contact with electricity.  Contact may be made directly from the power source to the person, such as touching a live wire or being struck by an electrical arc. Items that are intentionally electrified, such as electric fences, should be considered direct exposure to electricity (511). Indirect exposure (512) occurs when contacting an unintentionally electrified object. Household objects should be coded in the 220 volts or less  (5111 and 5121), while power lines and some industrial transformers should be coded in the greater than 220 volts  (5112 and 5122). When uncertain as to the voltage, assume household voltage to be 220 or less, and overhead wire voltage to be greater than 220.

635b72b5-9e33-4e75-8521-fbb2bfe48f00.title: Exposure to electricity— unspecified
635b72b5-9e33-4e75-8521-fbb2bfe48f00.definition: Exposure to electricity cases where it cannot be determined whether the exposure was direct or indirect
635b72b5-9e33-4e75-8521-fbb2bfe48f00.includes: Electrocuted; contact with electrified object like machines, power lines, and wiring; shocked

e7838d0a-1e3b-4dbb-bd25-7205cbd524ab.title: Direct exposure to electricity
e7838d0a-1e3b-4dbb-bd25-7205cbd524ab.definition: Codes in this group apply to injuries which are the result of direct electrical contact between the power source and the worker.
e7838d0a-1e3b-4dbb-bd25-7205cbd524ab.includes: Direct contact with power lines, wires and power sources; contact with intentionally electrified objects such as electric fences; power cords of equipment and machinery

be6506c0-cf31-45ec-8098-7cd78640a647.title: Direct exposure to electricity— unspecified
be6506c0-cf31-45ec-8098-7cd78640a647.definition: This code classifies cases resulting in injuries due to direct electrical contact between the power source and the person when the voltage cannot be determined.
be6506c0-cf31-45ec-8098-7cd78640a647.includes: Touched an electric wire without knowing if household or overhead
be6506c0-cf31-45ec-8098-7cd78640a647.excludes: Indirect contact with electricity (512); lightning strike (5112 or 5122); contact with a machine that becomes electrified, not just its electric parts (512)

249310f3-9bc9-4fed-b23d-bcdc2b0d572c.title: Direct exposure to electricity— 220 volts or less
249310f3-9bc9-4fed-b23d-bcdc2b0d572c.definition: This code classifies cases resulting in injuries due to direct electrical contact between the power source and the person when the voltage is 220 volts or less or described as household.
249310f3-9bc9-4fed-b23d-bcdc2b0d572c.includes: Direct contact with interior household electrical wiring or power cords

8391f868-e276-4225-b868-09a2c44d93d4.title: Direct exposure to electricity— greater than 220 volts
8391f868-e276-4225-b868-09a2c44d93d4.definition: This code classifies cases resulting in electrical injuries due to direct contact between the power source and the person when the voltage is greater than 220 volts

b46fc572-2dda-4450-bfb0-b01edb492c72.title: Indirect exposure to electricity
b46fc572-2dda-4450-bfb0-b01edb492c72.definition: Codes in this group apply to injuries that are the result of indirect exposure to electricity. Indirect exposure includes contact with objects which are not intended to be electrified, such as when a conductive material touches a source of electricity.
b46fc572-2dda-4450-bfb0-b01edb492c72.includes: Object held by worker contacts a power line
b46fc572-2dda-4450-bfb0-b01edb492c72.excludes: powered objects such as a crane touching a power line in a nontransportation capacity

cfad4e6d-d015-4844-b416-a62c7e8cbb84.title: Indirect exposure to electricity— unspecified
cfad4e6d-d015-4844-b416-a62c7e8cbb84.definition: Incidents involving indirect electrical contact between the power source and the person when the voltage cannot be determined
cfad4e6d-d015-4844-b416-a62c7e8cbb84.includes: Contact with a machine that becomes electrified

7312fb7d-88f9-4ae4-832d-3f7f391115fd.title: Indirect exposure to electricity— 220 volts or less
7312fb7d-88f9-4ae4-832d-3f7f391115fd.definition: This code classifies cases resulting in electrical injuries due to indirect contact between the power source and the person when the voltage is 220 volts or less
7312fb7d-88f9-4ae4-832d-3f7f391115fd.includes: Electric shock from sticking a fork into a toaster

67e78dda-5587-4490-8d07-3659c7cba2f1.title: Indirect exposure to electricity— greater than 220 volts
67e78dda-5587-4490-8d07-3659c7cba2f1.definition: This code classifies cases resulting in injuries due to indirect electrical contact between the power source and the person when the voltage is greater than 220 volts
67e78dda-5587-4490-8d07-3659c7cba2f1.includes: Tools or equipment that become energized by contacting a power line
67e78dda-5587-4490-8d07-3659c7cba2f1.excludes: contact with object energized by lightning

e731a1c7-a174-4f03-b522-2d13a30812ec.title: Exposure to electric arc
e731a1c7-a174-4f03-b522-2d13a30812ec.definition: Codes in this group apply to injuries which are the result of exposure to electric arc thermal energy. They typically result in burned charred clothing and skin burn on body, arms, legs and face/head as opposed to internal burns resulting from electric shock.
e731a1c7-a174-4f03-b522-2d13a30812ec.includes: Arc flash, arc blast, arc explosion

2911ce86-93e5-4fab-ad42-374ef325f820.title: Exposure to radiation and noise
2911ce86-93e5-4fab-ad42-374ef325f820.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are a result of exposure to all types of electromagnetic radiation as well as sound.

81e06828-2ff6-4199-b71b-a5d67d6fb471.title: Exposure to radiation and noise— unspecified
81e06828-2ff6-4199-b71b-a5d67d6fb471.definition: This code classifies injuries resulting from exposure to electromagnetic radiation waves or sound waves when the type of waves are unknown.

0b935e60-c5ef-4cdc-8086-6fa0312f87ea.title: Exposure to particle radiation— duration unspecified
0b935e60-c5ef-4cdc-8086-6fa0312f87ea.definition: This code classifies injuries that are the result of exposure to particle radiation where duration is unknown.

70889919-1a64-45b0-90d8-a19ed4f93ce2.title: Exposure to particle radiation— single episode or single shift
70889919-1a64-45b0-90d8-a19ed4f93ce2.definition: This code classifies injuries that are the result of exposure to particle radiation from a single episode or in a single shift.
70889919-1a64-45b0-90d8-a19ed4f93ce2.includes: Workers become ill after nuclear power plant radiation leak

7045cd81-12c9-4f5b-b1d9-8813032ad2fc.title: Exposure to particle radiation— repeated or prolonged
7045cd81-12c9-4f5b-b1d9-8813032ad2fc.definition: This code classifies injuries that are the result of repeated exposure to particle radiation over the course of more than one shift of work
7045cd81-12c9-4f5b-b1d9-8813032ad2fc.includes: Radiologist experiences health issues after exceeding radiation exposure limits for her job

b443944a-38d7-4740-9724-008ba78af820.title: Exposure to light, other radiation
b443944a-38d7-4740-9724-008ba78af820.definition: Codes in this group apply to injuries that are the result of exposure to other types of radiation, except as described in 521
b443944a-38d7-4740-9724-008ba78af820.includes: Exposure to microwaves and radio waves, radars, x-rays, and other power frequencies; strobing lights
b443944a-38d7-4740-9724-008ba78af820.excludes: Sunstroke and other environmental heat-related incidents (531); explosion injuries from arc flash, arc blast (31)

676e4e05-58fb-43a1-add2-7bbd4581a02e.title: Exposure to light, other radiation— duration unspecified
676e4e05-58fb-43a1-add2-7bbd4581a02e.definition: This code applies to injuries that are the result of exposure to infrared radiation, visible light, ultraviolet radiation or other radiation. While eye injuries are the most common, injuries to skin and other parts of body are also included. Injuries may be acute, such as laser injuries, or result from prolonged exposure. Cases where light was deemed to have played a role in exacerbating an underlying medical condition or provoking a reaction to medication should still be coded here, unless the reaction was due to non-medical use of drugs (Event 551).

dfd57d8d-8c9f-4d6f-b7e7-caa80e1e7b11.title: Exposure to light, other radiation— single episode or single shift
dfd57d8d-8c9f-4d6f-b7e7-caa80e1e7b11.definition: This code classifies injuries that are the result of exposure to light and other types of radiation from a single episode or in a single shift.
dfd57d8d-8c9f-4d6f-b7e7-caa80e1e7b11.includes: Flash burns from viewing ultraviolet (UV) light;  sunburn and sun poisoning; eye injuries from laser beams or electrical sparks; exposure to laser, infrared light, sunlight, and welding flash, welder's flash; blue light (screen) exposure; strobe lights

2007096c-2193-40c6-9289-ed40d8a1d3c2.title: Exposure to light, other radiation— repeated or prolonged
2007096c-2193-40c6-9289-ed40d8a1d3c2.definition: This code classifies injuries that are the result of repeated exposure to light and other types of radiation over the course of more than one shift of work

516f87b9-fd7c-4de5-afcf-fea6c84d7a86.title: Exposure to noise
516f87b9-fd7c-4de5-afcf-fea6c84d7a86.definition: Codes in this  group apply only to injuries that are the result of exposure to noise. Hearing impairments resulting from exposure to a single loud noise (with the exception of explosions) or to prolonged noise are classified here. Use code 5231 if the exposure was prolonged but was limited to a single shift. Use code 5232 for repeated exposures to noise over more than one shift.

a51bce9f-8be0-49b4-9cd1-f4874f49139f.title: Exposure to noise— duration unspecified
a51bce9f-8be0-49b4-9cd1-f4874f49139f.definition: This code classifies injuries where the duration of the exposure to noise is unknown.
a51bce9f-8be0-49b4-9cd1-f4874f49139f.includes: Cases where duration of exposure (brief, prolonged, and repeated) cannot be determined

cdc90e3c-9cfa-4f73-a087-ce70472e038a.title: Exposure to noise— single episode or single shift
cdc90e3c-9cfa-4f73-a087-ce70472e038a.definition: This code classifies injuries due to a single, brief noise event.

00ac3fd0-0fce-444e-9f2e-af89479dbf0b.title: Exposure to noise— repeated or prolonged
00ac3fd0-0fce-444e-9f2e-af89479dbf0b.definition: This code classifies injuries due to long term exposure to noise in the workplace for longer than one shift.
00ac3fd0-0fce-444e-9f2e-af89479dbf0b.includes: Hearing loss from machinery noise over more than one shift; hearing loss due to working on the airport tarmac, longer than one shift

b422961f-690d-40df-ac01-785e6fe93cd3.title: Exposure to temperature extremes
b422961f-690d-40df-ac01-785e6fe93cd3.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of exposure to general heat or cold in the environment (531 or 532) or from contact with hot or cold objects or substances (533 or 534).

35769a11-6281-4e94-977e-297f315711e2.title: Exposure to temperature extremes— unspecified
35769a11-6281-4e94-977e-297f315711e2.definition: This code classifies injuries resulting from temperature extremes when the exposure cannot be determined to be from heat or cold or from the environment or an object.

8c05673a-f0a4-4eb9-9ff9-8e8692de09c2.title: Exposure to environmental heat
8c05673a-f0a4-4eb9-9ff9-8e8692de09c2.definition: This code classifies injuries and illnesses resulting from ambient heat and high temperatures in the workplace where direct contact with a heated object did not occur. Cases where heat was deemed to have played a role in exacerbating an underlying medical condition or provoking a reaction to medication should still be coded here, unless the reaction was due to non-medical use of drugs (551).
8c05673a-f0a4-4eb9-9ff9-8e8692de09c2.includes: Heat exhaustion, heat stroke, hyperthermia, or fatigue from high temperatures in any work environment; working around furnaces, kilns or other heat producing equipment without direct contact with hot objects
8c05673a-f0a4-4eb9-9ff9-8e8692de09c2.excludes: Injuries from exposure to the sun's rays or other electromagnetic radiations (522)

e4176e21-6e04-4ae3-a84b-d8593a2253f4.title: Exposure to environmental heat— indoor
e4176e21-6e04-4ae3-a84b-d8593a2253f4.includes: Worker experienced effects of heat after working in boiler room

99f9ee16-312b-41ef-a8fd-7b64ef716229.title: Exposure to environmental heat— outdoor
99f9ee16-312b-41ef-a8fd-7b64ef716229.includes: Worker experienced heat stroke after working outside on a hot day

b15d3187-fdc4-4d0c-82f3-82542d2df766.title: Exposure to environmental cold
b15d3187-fdc4-4d0c-82f3-82542d2df766.definition: This code classifies injuries and illnesses resulting from cold temperatures in the workplace where direct contact with a cold object did not occur.

5adcd1b8-596a-4e7f-b2be-4a4fe9e795fc.title: Exposure to environmental cold— indoor
5adcd1b8-596a-4e7f-b2be-4a4fe9e795fc.includes: Worker was accidently locked in freezer

0f8b0f05-b0f7-4cb1-8160-04af90537696.title: Exposure to environmental cold— outdoor
0f8b0f05-b0f7-4cb1-8160-04af90537696.includes: Worker experienced hypothermia after working outdoors

58a779c5-faf7-4aed-958b-16ff1f5ad737.title: Contact with hot objects or substances
58a779c5-faf7-4aed-958b-16ff1f5ad737.definition: This code classifies injuries due to contact with hot objects or substances.
58a779c5-faf7-4aed-958b-16ff1f5ad737.includes: Contact with heat sources such as stoves, welding torches, or hot fluids; contact with fire and flames from stoves, campfires, torches, cigarettes, furnaces, etc. and radiant heat emitted from such sources; contact with objects that are hot due to environmental heat such as metal object heated by exposure to the sun
58a779c5-faf7-4aed-958b-16ff1f5ad737.excludes: Unintentional and uncontrolled fires and explosions (Division 3)

e0ef9ad4-a2ea-49e4-9a6b-d87ba99208ac.title: Contact with cold objects or substances
e0ef9ad4-a2ea-49e4-9a6b-d87ba99208ac.definition: This code classifies injuries due to contact with cold objects or substances.
e0ef9ad4-a2ea-49e4-9a6b-d87ba99208ac.includes: contact with dry ice, freezer surfaces, liquid nitrogen, etc.; contact with objects that are cold due to environmental cold, such as outside metal signs, light poles, etc.
e0ef9ad4-a2ea-49e4-9a6b-d87ba99208ac.excludes: injuries and illnesses from environmental cold (532)

7de4137d-65c1-4f88-9db6-b42647c505ca.title: Exposure to air and water pressure change
7de4137d-65c1-4f88-9db6-b42647c505ca.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of bodily reaction to changes in air and water pressure.

b4b1467d-25e5-4759-a6c9-56a27f397a6e.title: Exposure to air and water pressure change— unspecified
b4b1467d-25e5-4759-a6c9-56a27f397a6e.definition: This code classifies injuries from bodily reactions to changes in pressure when it is unknown whether air pressure or water pressure was responsible.
b4b1467d-25e5-4759-a6c9-56a27f397a6e.includes: Decompression illness when the medium of pressure cannot be determined

25a67644-ba08-4ba1-98cc-850ec9e14d6f.title: Exposure to change in water pressure
25a67644-ba08-4ba1-98cc-850ec9e14d6f.definition: This code classifies injuries from bodily reactions to changes in water pressure.
25a67644-ba08-4ba1-98cc-850ec9e14d6f.includes: Decompression illness, caisson disease, or the bends due to diving

bc2d8d02-708e-44f4-a9e1-eba7542c12fc.title: Exposure to change in air pressure
bc2d8d02-708e-44f4-a9e1-eba7542c12fc.definition: This code classifies injuries from bodily reactions to changes in air pressure.
bc2d8d02-708e-44f4-a9e1-eba7542c12fc.excludes: Being struck by pressurized air being discharged from a hose or compressor (6421)

7736e392-0005-473f-a128-52f6ee28b443.title: Exposure to harmful substances
7736e392-0005-473f-a128-52f6ee28b443.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of the inhalation, absorption (skin contact), injection or needle stick, or ingestion of harmful substances.  Medical complications and sequelae, such a cut or laceration from an initial injury that becomes infected due to exposure, should be coded to the event which caused the initial injury.
7736e392-0005-473f-a128-52f6ee28b443.includes: Poisoning through inhalation or ingestion; exposure to allergens; contagious and infectious diseases; drug overdoses; exposure to caustic, noxious, allergenic substances, drugs, infectious agents

b910765f-84e0-4053-bb5c-5ebd1ba6df1e.title: Exposure to harmful substances— unspecified
b910765f-84e0-4053-bb5c-5ebd1ba6df1e.definition: Injuries that are a result of exposure to harmful substances when a more specific code from 551 to 558 cannot be determined.
b910765f-84e0-4053-bb5c-5ebd1ba6df1e.includes: Exposure via a human or animal vector when the specific route of exposure is unknown

21e7da18-d2de-4dd5-90aa-26b0945c48f8.title: Drug, alcohol overdose
21e7da18-d2de-4dd5-90aa-26b0945c48f8.definition: Overdoses from drugs and alcohol that were not prescribed by a physician or were not used according to prescription, regardless of delivery mechanism when self-harm was unintentional or the intent to harm is unknown.
21e7da18-d2de-4dd5-90aa-26b0945c48f8.includes: Drug overdoses of unknown intention; intentional use of non-drug substances such as inhalants, grain alcohol, detergent pods, etc.
21e7da18-d2de-4dd5-90aa-26b0945c48f8.excludes: Accidental exposures to drugs, such as during manufacture, dispensing, or administration of a drug (552-559), or law enforcement activities; drugs taken in therapeutic use (552-559); vaccines (552, 553, 554); suicides and other purposeful injuries resulting from drugs (Division 1)

112f9355-66f0-483d-8712-566b19bef2d5.title: Reaction to prescribed medication or vaccines
112f9355-66f0-483d-8712-566b19bef2d5.definition: Reactions to medicines and vaccines used as prescribed by a medical professional. Medications may be taken via any delivery mechanism (ingestion, injection, etc.)

90549b51-ca0c-4056-8fcd-2d3259b4d043.title: Inhalation of harmful substance
90549b51-ca0c-4056-8fcd-2d3259b4d043.definition: Unintentional inhalation of gases or airborne particulates.
90549b51-ca0c-4056-8fcd-2d3259b4d043.includes: Inhalation of dust and fumes, inhalation of chemicals and smoke
90549b51-ca0c-4056-8fcd-2d3259b4d043.excludes: Choking on substance(562), drowning (56); intentional inhalation of substance for recreational purposes (551);  intentional inhalation of substance for self-harm purposes (125)

02606e2a-7ee0-4a87-aff8-1050602adc2f.title: Inhalation of harmful substance— unspecified
02606e2a-7ee0-4a87-aff8-1050602adc2f.definition: Inhalation of gases or airborne particulates where the length of time of the exposure is unknown.

43981125-1692-4102-92ef-f05ca76ae46d.title: Inhalation of harmful substance— single episode or single shift
43981125-1692-4102-92ef-f05ca76ae46d.definition: Inhalation of gases or airborne particulates limited to a single shift.
43981125-1692-4102-92ef-f05ca76ae46d.includes: Smoke inhalation in the absence of a fire or explosion

7b2de4fd-e969-4c9f-bea2-8f94074cf65f.title: Inhalation of harmful substance— repeated or prolonged
7b2de4fd-e969-4c9f-bea2-8f94074cf65f.definition: Inhalation of gases or airborne particulates that exceed a single shift or occur daily over a prolonged period.
7b2de4fd-e969-4c9f-bea2-8f94074cf65f.includes: Temp worker experienced respiratory symptoms after a week of being hire to paint house.
7b2de4fd-e969-4c9f-bea2-8f94074cf65f.excludes: Intentional self harm by inhalation of substance (125)

82219931-ef28-41d1-9f66-634f371a6c73.title: Ingestion of harmful substance
82219931-ef28-41d1-9f66-634f371a6c73.definition: Ingestion or digestion of a substance producing an adverse reaction.

214bc0a1-6c0a-490a-80cf-8d00fd9a35de.title: Exposure to harmful substance through exposed tissue
214bc0a1-6c0a-490a-80cf-8d00fd9a35de.definition: Codes in this group apply to exposure to harmful substances through skin, eyes, or other exposed tissue. Types of exposures may include chemicals or other caustic agents, allergens, infectious agents, and blood or body fluids.

f7d2a695-0572-4b64-a6ec-9d0d90053022.title: Exposure to harmful substance through exposed tissue— unspecified

175b9f98-c762-4528-8664-e5fed53467e5.title: Unintentional needlestick or sharps injury
175b9f98-c762-4528-8664-e5fed53467e5.definition: Exposures that are the result of unintentional contact with hypodermic needles and other medical sharps.
175b9f98-c762-4528-8664-e5fed53467e5.includes: Clean sharps and dirty sharps injuries

5d5eb2b9-19d3-4645-9929-30170e55c937.title: Exposure through wound or broken skin
5d5eb2b9-19d3-4645-9929-30170e55c937.definition: Exposure to harmful substances where the skin was already broken at the time of exposure. Types of exposures may include chemicals or other caustic agents, allergens, infectious agents, blood or body fluids
5d5eb2b9-19d3-4645-9929-30170e55c937.includes: Bodily fluid splash on open wound
5d5eb2b9-19d3-4645-9929-30170e55c937.excludes: exposure through already-present dermatitis or eczema

03f2ae8e-8b45-4333-bb7a-24855ae1bb01.title: Exposure through intact tissue
03f2ae8e-8b45-4333-bb7a-24855ae1bb01.definition: Exposure to harmful substances such as chemicals or other caustic agents, allergens, infectious agents, blood or body fluids where the skin was intact at the point of contact
03f2ae8e-8b45-4333-bb7a-24855ae1bb01.excludes: contact with harmful substances through eyes

50c0aac9-79d7-447e-bb1d-ca39d92afd35.title: Multiple types of exposure through exposed tissue

feb76228-a912-4414-a771-c6ec1bb3d040.title: Exposure to harmful substance through exposed tissue— n.e.c.

4c9beb85-26e2-49cb-8114-6d2af693799c.title: Exposure to harmful substance—multiple routes of exposure
4c9beb85-26e2-49cb-8114-6d2af693799c.definition: Combination of two or more different exposures from groups 552 to 555.

753c06b6-7e5d-4a99-a39f-157d731a41b3.title: Exposure to other harmful substances— n.e.c.

cf75f132-f19d-4e1b-b174-a0d5c74b0f96.title: Exposure to oxygen deficiency
cf75f132-f19d-4e1b-b174-a0d5c74b0f96.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of lack of oxygen without the involvement of harmful substances and when no other event category applies. Drowning and nonfatal submersions are classified here if no other event applies.
cf75f132-f19d-4e1b-b174-a0d5c74b0f96.excludes: Intentional strangulations or asphyxiations (Division 1); drowning and submersions from transportation incidents (Division 2); asphyxiations from fires and explosions (Division 3); drowning and submersions that result from falls (Division 4); asphyxiation due to inhalation of harmful substance, alone or in combination with oxygen deficient environment (553);  oxygen deficient environments and physical restriction of breathing resulting from cave-ins or engulfments (63);  strangulations from being caught in running equipment (65)

e8e23b6b-ecf6-41e8-ad2a-e7cbea6cbdb3.title: Exposure to oxygen deficiency— unspecified
e8e23b6b-ecf6-41e8-ad2a-e7cbea6cbdb3.definition: Injuries due to oxygen deficiency where the cause cannot be determined.

82959fa6-48fb-4213-b7e4-03af8fa5df5d.title: Drowning, submersion without other event
82959fa6-48fb-4213-b7e4-03af8fa5df5d.excludes: diver running out of air while underwater

41b7122d-e360-42f5-8939-2b20098ecf80.title: Choking on object or substance
41b7122d-e360-42f5-8939-2b20098ecf80.definition: Injuries where the windpipe is physically blocked by an object or substance injected.
41b7122d-e360-42f5-8939-2b20098ecf80.includes: Worker chokes on food at desk
41b7122d-e360-42f5-8939-2b20098ecf80.excludes: Injuries sustained through abdominal thrusts or Heimlich Maneuver (66)

2d12c980-14af-407f-bc41-7d6b57fae337.title: Oxygen displacement
2d12c980-14af-407f-bc41-7d6b57fae337.definition: Injuries that are a result of oxygen being displaced by another gas.
2d12c980-14af-407f-bc41-7d6b57fae337.excludes: Oxygen within a space being displaced by harmful gas (5531)

13103a01-f710-4eb8-b64e-db81c989c01a.title: Exposure to oxygen deficiency— n.e.c.
13103a01-f710-4eb8-b64e-db81c989c01a.definition: Oxygen deficiency that is known but does not fit descriptions of codes 561 and 563.

ca8617c9-e616-42f6-8188-0ffb3e2bc2fd.title: Exposure to stressful environment without other event
ca8617c9-e616-42f6-8188-0ffb3e2bc2fd.definition: This code applies to events where the worker is affected by stressful events on the job with the exception of being a victim or witness of violent act(s) or threatening actions provoking a reasonable fear of violence. Stress from being involved in another event such as a transportation incident or fire should be coded to that event. Assume events and actions of persons are unintentional unless source documents support clear intent to harm oneself or another person.
ca8617c9-e616-42f6-8188-0ffb3e2bc2fd.includes: Stress from workplace harassment or hazing without reasonable fear of harm or violence; stressful work environment; reactions to workplace critiques, disciplinary actions, or perceived "unfairness"; fear of losing job
ca8617c9-e616-42f6-8188-0ffb3e2bc2fd.excludes: Events where the worker was a victim of or witness to an assault or violent act ( Divison1)

4d5dd7a1-62dc-4d7e-bf98-688581e836c8.title: Exposure to stressful environment without other event— duration unspecified
4d5dd7a1-62dc-4d7e-bf98-688581e836c8.definition: Exposure to workplace stress of unknown duration

e67e5340-5801-4458-94c1-41dfe9353634.title: Exposure to stressful environment— prolonged
e67e5340-5801-4458-94c1-41dfe9353634.definition: Exposure to a workplace stressor for longer than one shift
e67e5340-5801-4458-94c1-41dfe9353634.includes: Ongoing harassment or hazing without reasonable fear of harm or violence; "toxic work environment"

d30b4b46-7610-4e32-a55b-7c79f017fe13.title: Exposure to stressful environment— single episode
d30b4b46-7610-4e32-a55b-7c79f017fe13.definition: Stress resulting from witnessing a single traumatic, non violent work event where the worker was not the direct victim of the incident.

41f9b666-7d6a-4247-9724-ee21d030a059.title: Exposure to harmful substances or environments— n.e.c.
41f9b666-7d6a-4247-9724-ee21d030a059.definition: This code includes events that are the result of exposure to harmful substances or environments but do not match codes 50 through 572.

4abb865e-a3fc-4944-92d5-61774130fbde.title: CONTACT INCIDENTS
4abb865e-a3fc-4944-92d5-61774130fbde.definition: Codes in this division apply to injuries that are the result of contact between the injured person and the source of injury, except when the contact was due to a fall, transportation incident, fire or explosion, or assault or violent act by a person. This division also excludes contact with harmful substances. The contact can be with a stationary or moving object, equipment, person, or animal.

f0d03c7b-8738-4b35-9cf3-9c179098eb3a.title: Contact incidents— unspecified
f0d03c7b-8738-4b35-9cf3-9c179098eb3a.definition: Contact between the injured person and stationary or moving object, equipment, person or animal, when a more specific code from 61 to 69 cannot be determined.

f4aced01-bba3-45fd-8501-fe5061a75496.title: Contact with other person, nonviolent or intent unknown
f4aced01-bba3-45fd-8501-fe5061a75496.definition: Codes in this major group apply to incidents that are the result of nonviolent, intentional or incidental physical contact with another person(s). Physical contact that is clearly of violent intent are coded in Violence (11). Those with unknown intent are considered to be unintentional and coded here. Overexertion injuries are coded in Division 7.
f4aced01-bba3-45fd-8501-fe5061a75496.excludes: Intentional violent contact (11); contact with item (except sports equipment) wielded by another person (6621); physical contact due to the motion of a vehicle in transport (Division 2); overexertion injuries while caregiving (711); exposures to infectious agents or contagious diseases, even if the exposure is a result of contact with a person (55)

494ce492-66e4-4923-9731-97edcff50dd9.title: Contact with other person, nonviolent or intent unknown—  unspecified
494ce492-66e4-4923-9731-97edcff50dd9.definition: Injuries resulting from direct physical contact with a person when a more specific code from 611 to 619 cannot be determined

c6f2ab58-3f75-4221-a110-dab40f06dd07.title: Contact with other person, equipment during sports or physical training
c6f2ab58-3f75-4221-a110-dab40f06dd07.definition: Accidental or intentional physical contact with the body or sports equipment of another person(s) during sports or fitness competition or training
c6f2ab58-3f75-4221-a110-dab40f06dd07.excludes: injuries resulting from physical contact during staged fight

c997d779-b158-46b0-8860-49d927818202.title: Contact with other person while providing medical or custodial care
c997d779-b158-46b0-8860-49d927818202.definition: Accidental or incidental physical contact with the body of another person(s) while rescuing or providing care to patients, children, or other charges. Injuries that are solely the result of a care provider overexerting over a patient should be coded in 711.
c997d779-b158-46b0-8860-49d927818202.includes: Injuries while rescuing; providing care for children or special needs persons; providing medical care, nursing care; unintentionally struck by patient; non-violent contact with social work clients, students

424a45ab-099f-40b0-888c-7ee5010b3901.title: Contact with other person, nonviolent or intent unknown— n.e.c.
424a45ab-099f-40b0-888c-7ee5010b3901.definition: Accidental or intentional physical contact with another person(s) that does not meet descriptions of codes 661-662.
424a45ab-099f-40b0-888c-7ee5010b3901.includes: Contact injuries as a result of horseplay; accidental contact, such as an coworkers colliding with one another; bumping heads

d7b6cc71-93b7-43f0-a210-0b01a2e00609.title: Contact with animals
d7b6cc71-93b7-43f0-a210-0b01a2e00609.definition: Codes in this major group describe incidents where a worker is harmed as a result of direct contact with an animal, regardless of the animal's intent to harm the person.

0a0f8c27-7475-4557-af7c-1838b8eda36f.title: Contact with animals— unspecified
0a0f8c27-7475-4557-af7c-1838b8eda36f.definition: Contact with a non-venomous animal when a more specific event code from 621 to 629 cannot be determined

6574570c-04df-464e-b3fd-c9253dd4e0b3.title: Bitten or stung by animal
6574570c-04df-464e-b3fd-c9253dd4e0b3.definition: Injuries resulting from being bitten by a non-venomous animal

9197eb6e-7725-427e-931b-ad9a8043f85d.title: Bitten or stung by animal— unspecified
9197eb6e-7725-427e-931b-ad9a8043f85d.definition: Injuries resulting from being bitten or stung by an animal when a more specific code from 6211 to 6213 cannot be determined

548fcbdb-5523-493f-b938-cf260a958d20.title: Bite or sting— insects, "bugs"
548fcbdb-5523-493f-b938-cf260a958d20.definition: Bites and stings from all types of "bugs". That is insects, arachnids, and myriapods (e.g. centipedes). Use this code regardless of whether the creature is considered venomous or not and whether or not the bite transmitted an illness, such as Lyme disease, West Nile virus, etc.
548fcbdb-5523-493f-b938-cf260a958d20.includes: Spider and scorpion bites and stings
548fcbdb-5523-493f-b938-cf260a958d20.excludes: allergic reactions due to insect bites

b6fc53fe-71fa-4090-a609-d1ef09003128.title: Venomous animal bite— except "bugs"
b6fc53fe-71fa-4090-a609-d1ef09003128.definition: Venomous animal bite or contact, excluding bites and stings from bugs.

806c260c-093b-41ca-a354-65a596b28995.title: Non-venomous animal bites— except "bugs"
806c260c-093b-41ca-a354-65a596b28995.definition: Injuries resulting from being bitten by a non- venomous animal

8eebc4c6-2b9f-47d7-b4f5-1d74e0e4b59d.title: Struck by animal— unspecified
8eebc4c6-2b9f-47d7-b4f5-1d74e0e4b59d.definition: Contact with a non-venomous animal, except bites, when a more specific event code from 6221 to 6229 cannot be determined.
8eebc4c6-2b9f-47d7-b4f5-1d74e0e4b59d.includes: Contact with cow with no other information

8616c4e5-9e4e-4586-809d-560575181515.title: Gored, rammed by animal
8616c4e5-9e4e-4586-809d-560575181515.definition: Contact with a charging or butting animal with or without puncture by a horn.

c741197b-5405-455e-bb82-5098d6ecb675.title: Stepped on, kicked, trampled by animal
c741197b-5405-455e-bb82-5098d6ecb675.excludes: knocked down and run over by running goats

3d7388b1-0785-40e3-8e4e-657e330a3670.title: Struck by animal— n.e.c.
3d7388b1-0785-40e3-8e4e-657e330a3670.definition: Contact with animal that does not fit descriptions of codes 6220-6223
3d7388b1-0785-40e3-8e4e-657e330a3670.includes: Struck by flying animal such as birds and bats

a05eba9a-0dee-4409-9c42-ae04cd84d75a.title: Multiple types of contact with animals
a05eba9a-0dee-4409-9c42-ae04cd84d75a.definition: Combination of one of more contact codes from 620 to 6229.
a05eba9a-0dee-4409-9c42-ae04cd84d75a.includes: Scratched and bitten by a cat

a6a29b63-b18f-4b30-a03f-8c2e5443ed8b.title: Contact with animals— n.e.c.
a6a29b63-b18f-4b30-a03f-8c2e5443ed8b.definition: Contact with animals when a more specific event code that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes from 621 to 628.
a6a29b63-b18f-4b30-a03f-8c2e5443ed8b.includes: Contact with poisonous or allergenic animal, such as jelly fish; spit on; sat on; animal falling on person; animal throws feces; contact with quills or barbs

e32ce040-e381-4c61-b4f2-4fc5676c83da.title: Collapse, engulfment
e32ce040-e381-4c61-b4f2-4fc5676c83da.definition: Codes in this major group apply to incidents that are the result of a being struck by a collapsing structure or equipment or an engulfment in material.
e32ce040-e381-4c61-b4f2-4fc5676c83da.includes: Compression, crushing, depletion of oxygen or drowning from cave-in or collapse; struck by falling debris during cave-in or collapse
e32ce040-e381-4c61-b4f2-4fc5676c83da.excludes: Collapse caused by fire or explosion (Division 3)

e7a0a990-2c7a-4411-98e8-69f6287eda36.title: Collapse, engulfment— unspecified
e7a0a990-2c7a-4411-98e8-69f6287eda36.definition: Collapse of or engulfment in structures or material when a more specific event code from 6310 to 6390 cannot be determined.
e7a0a990-2c7a-4411-98e8-69f6287eda36.excludes: Falls resulting from structure or equipment collapse (Division 4)

d76afa4d-bcc1-474c-ae7a-2a6f4f82685a.title: Collapse, engulfment— closed mine or tunnel
d76afa4d-bcc1-474c-ae7a-2a6f4f82685a.definition: Collapse of closed tunnel or mine
d76afa4d-bcc1-474c-ae7a-2a6f4f82685a.includes: Partial collapse of mine wall or roof

3b9b245b-c719-41a5-a23c-0deb7510912a.title: Collapse, engulfment— open trench or excavation
3b9b245b-c719-41a5-a23c-0deb7510912a.definition: Collapse or cave-in of any man-made cut, cavity, trench, or depression in the earth’s surface formed by earth removal
3b9b245b-c719-41a5-a23c-0deb7510912a.excludes: removed earth falling back into the excavation

a0b674ac-6775-47ab-a77f-900bbeb32b1a.title: Collapse, engulfment— loose materials or liquids
a0b674ac-6775-47ab-a77f-900bbeb32b1a.definition: Partial or total engulfment in loose materials or liquids. May involve sinking into materials or being overtaken by collapsing or surging materials
a0b674ac-6775-47ab-a77f-900bbeb32b1a.includes: Collapsing grain; sinking in loose materials; quicksand; manure pits; collapse or surge of materials due to natural disasters including tsunami, tidal wave, flood waters, rockslide, mudslide, avalanche
a0b674ac-6775-47ab-a77f-900bbeb32b1a.excludes: Falls into liquids or loose materials (Division 4)

819536f4-20b5-406c-a953-078a90c0c68e.title: Collapse, engulfment— building or structure
819536f4-20b5-406c-a953-078a90c0c68e.definition: Struck by or buried in materials breaking loose from buildings and structures in the process of full or partial collapse. Person may be in or on collapsing structure or outside within striking distance of materials.
819536f4-20b5-406c-a953-078a90c0c68e.excludes: struck by debris from ceiling collapse

94d2a3a8-941d-462a-9347-2d1804f3d06c.title: Collapse, engulfment— n.e.c.
94d2a3a8-941d-462a-9347-2d1804f3d06c.definition: Collapse or engulfment event that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 631 to 634
94d2a3a8-941d-462a-9347-2d1804f3d06c.excludes: struck by collapsing boom (except permanent and semi-permanent tower cranes)

b0b03374-9ef4-4e91-8fc1-d016eab0027b.title: Struck by propelled, falling, or suspended object
b0b03374-9ef4-4e91-8fc1-d016eab0027b.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of being struck by a propelled object or substance; self-propelled flying object; or falling, discharged, dislodged or detached objects.
b0b03374-9ef4-4e91-8fc1-d016eab0027b.includes: Thrown ball or other object; self-propelled flying object; discarded, dislodged or detached objects; free falling objects; objects dropped by a person; objects falling from running equipment

81597518-39fe-46c1-9fa1-8a76d2aa31f1.title: Struck by propelled, falling, or suspended object— unspecified
81597518-39fe-46c1-9fa1-8a76d2aa31f1.definition: Struck by a propelled object or substance self-propelled flying object or falling, discharged, dislodged or detached objects when a more specific event code from 641 to 6429 cannot be determined.

8c623e86-795b-4cf7-8cd0-642934f9ce99.title: Gun discharge— accidental or intent unknown
8c623e86-795b-4cf7-8cd0-642934f9ce99.definition: Shot by firearm due to accidental discharge or when fired in a nonviolent situation. The shooter can be either the injured worker or another person.
8c623e86-795b-4cf7-8cd0-642934f9ce99.includes: Gun discharged while cleaning; accidently shot during hunting trip; accidental harm from shooting during training exercise, sport

1d31add4-e901-48aa-bf95-ff222325a063.title: Struck by propelled object or substance
1d31add4-e901-48aa-bf95-ff222325a063.definition: Struck by objects or substances that have been thrown, hurled, or propelled across space.
1d31add4-e901-48aa-bf95-ff222325a063.includes: Thrown ball or other object; self-propelled flying object; discarded, dislodged or detached objects; discharged or flying objects

1ae03763-ade2-48f0-a419-17471b47de87.title: Struck by propelled object or substance— unspecified
1ae03763-ade2-48f0-a419-17471b47de87.definition: Struck by objects or substances that have been thrown, hurled, or propelled across space when a more specific code from 6421 to 6429 cannot be determined.

433d4e9b-d23a-41e8-8b89-f4ea17d8ba50.title: Struck by discharged object or substance
433d4e9b-d23a-41e8-8b89-f4ea17d8ba50.definition: Struck by object(s) that are sprayed or discharged under power or pressure, usually by a tool or equipment designed for that purpose.
433d4e9b-d23a-41e8-8b89-f4ea17d8ba50.includes: Air compressor blasts, power washer blasts, fire hose, nail gun
433d4e9b-d23a-41e8-8b89-f4ea17d8ba50.excludes: Struck by a flying piece or particle that has broken off an object (6422)

d98456c7-f5a6-4d69-a86d-470c6bb52d0a.title: Struck by dislodged or detached object(s)
d98456c7-f5a6-4d69-a86d-470c6bb52d0a.definition: Struck by dislodged flying object or particle when a piece of material separates from or breaks off of a tool, machine, or other object that is not intended to separate.
d98456c7-f5a6-4d69-a86d-470c6bb52d0a.includes: Flying broken glass or other particles; a piece of grinding wheel flying off; tire rims flying off (unless the tire or rim exploded); piece of material separating from a tool; rope, chain or fastener snapping
d98456c7-f5a6-4d69-a86d-470c6bb52d0a.excludes: Air compressor blasts, power washer blasts, fire hose, nail gun, accidentally discharged by another person (6421); accidentally discharged gun (BB, stun, paintball) (641); items kicked back by machinery without being thrown or becoming detached, saw kickback (651); explosions (31)

c08f1bd0-1549-4662-b1ec-78025098c9d7.title: Struck by other propelled object or substance— n.e.c.
c08f1bd0-1549-4662-b1ec-78025098c9d7.definition: Struck by an object being propelled across space that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes  6421 to 6422.

3ade728b-7d26-460b-8091-23c8db01f123.title: Struck by falling object
3ade728b-7d26-460b-8091-23c8db01f123.definition: Struck by objects and equipment slipping or falling freely by force of gravity.
3ade728b-7d26-460b-8091-23c8db01f123.includes: Objects and equipment tipping over, dropped by a person or falling from running equipment such as a conveyor; unattached items that are slipping or sliding off of a surface
3ade728b-7d26-460b-8091-23c8db01f123.excludes: Struck by falling doors, still attached (e.g. garage doors) (6441)

e70d4f69-78f0-41ff-b948-4e8afef54bf3.title: Struck by falling object— unspecified
e70d4f69-78f0-41ff-b948-4e8afef54bf3.definition: Struck by objects falling freely downward by force of gravity where a more specific code from 6431 to 6439 cannot be determined.
e70d4f69-78f0-41ff-b948-4e8afef54bf3.excludes: Objects being propelled by a force other than gravity (642)

80cf5c66-feb3-4ccd-8ddf-8e03f784e607.title: Struck by object dropped by person
80cf5c66-feb3-4ccd-8ddf-8e03f784e607.definition: Struck by object of any size dropped by or falling from the injured worker or by another person
