80cf5c66-feb3-4ccd-8ddf-8e03f784e607.excludes: items dropped from roof onto workers below

dadc3721-d699-4d85-9836-6d9d83e31b20.title: Struck by object tipping over
dadc3721-d699-4d85-9836-6d9d83e31b20.definition: Struck by any object or equipment that is self supporting on the ground surface tipping over but not moving under power and not the result of a collapse.
dadc3721-d699-4d85-9836-6d9d83e31b20.includes: Outrigger failure, shelf or file cabinet tipping over
dadc3721-d699-4d85-9836-6d9d83e31b20.excludes: Collapsing structures or equipment (634); boom collapse (634); struck by objects as a result of transportation incidents (Division2), fires or explosions (Division 3)

49a943a2-fc82-4033-b94f-d0f0f1b8e363.title: Struck by falling part of vehicle or machine, still attached
49a943a2-fc82-4033-b94f-d0f0f1b8e363.definition: Struck by attached parts of vehicles or equipment that fall or descend in an uncontrolled fashion.

4a1cc573-6eef-4524-94b2-c293dadbd731.title: Struck by other falling object— n.e.c.
4a1cc573-6eef-4524-94b2-c293dadbd731.definition: Struck by a falling object event that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 6431 to 6433. The object is free falling and not dropped by a person, not falling from running equipment and not a tipping over.

4c0b538f-7fa9-4684-8341-7cb9211e68fa.title: Struck by suspended or swinging object
4c0b538f-7fa9-4684-8341-7cb9211e68fa.definition: Events where the worker was struck by objects and equipment parts that are suspended or swinging from a fixed point. It excludes handheld objects. The item(s) may be suspended from powered equipment or non-powered fixed points.

c919ce7c-6c4d-477e-acf9-30cadb034853.title: Struck by suspended or swinging objects— unspecified

23c66e89-a5bf-4425-a2e9-7226ebbeb334.title: Struck by door, gate, window
23c66e89-a5bf-4425-a2e9-7226ebbeb334.definition: Powered or nonpowered doors, gates, or windows that may be raising, lowering or swinging from hinges
23c66e89-a5bf-4425-a2e9-7226ebbeb334.includes: Hand and caught in vehicle door, struck by lowering garage door, caught in revolving door, hand caught in powered or nonpowered window

ae526a65-605f-48c1-ae53-19336dd47144.title: Struck by suspended or swinging objects— n.e.c.
ae526a65-605f-48c1-ae53-19336dd47144.definition: Struck by parts or objects that are suspended or swinging from an object or equipment
ae526a65-605f-48c1-ae53-19336dd47144.includes: Struck by crane block or load
ae526a65-605f-48c1-ae53-19336dd47144.excludes: items suspended on nonpowered track (gantry crane)

8bd61556-39e7-4b6b-97e3-2cda1785c733.title: Struck by propelled, falling, or suspended object— n.e.c.

fd8f7549-7344-47f7-835d-75ad5887673c.title: Struck, caught, or compressed by running powered equipment
fd8f7549-7344-47f7-835d-75ad5887673c.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of the motion all types of equipment and machinery running under power, except discharged, falling, or suspended and swinging objects. Incidents are assumed to occur during normal operation unless case documents indicate otherwise. The detailed codes describe what kind of machine motion produced the harmful contact between worker and machine.
fd8f7549-7344-47f7-835d-75ad5887673c.includes: Contact with running machinery and equipment including industrial machinery, mobile equipment (except during transport); running, powered hand-wielded equipment; includes running water or water hoses (assume powered by pump)

979198ba-ff3e-4efc-9877-545a5f9a4b5d.title: Struck by running powered equipment— unspecified
979198ba-ff3e-4efc-9877-545a5f9a4b5d.definition: Contact with all types of equipment and machinery running under power, when a more specific code from 651 to 659 cannot be determined.
979198ba-ff3e-4efc-9877-545a5f9a4b5d.includes: Contact with running machinery and equipment including industrial machinery and mobile equipment (except during transport); running, powered hand-wielded equipment
979198ba-ff3e-4efc-9877-545a5f9a4b5d.excludes: Struck by running equipment being pushed by person (6622) or moving across a surface under power (unless contact was with moving machine parts) (653)

01f1682d-9044-4485-824a-672dc4d31046.title: Struck by running powered equipment— irregular movement, kick back
01f1682d-9044-4485-824a-672dc4d31046.definition: Contact or jarring resulting from machinery or materials being processed by machinery striking the worker due to recoil or sudden backward motion.
01f1682d-9044-4485-824a-672dc4d31046.excludes: kick back of wood being cut

375c06b2-ee56-433c-bf56-1dac02d0e301.title: Struck by running powered equipment— during maintenance, cleaning, testing
375c06b2-ee56-433c-bf56-1dac02d0e301.definition: Contact with powered equipment during non-normal operation. This may include unplanned repairs and interventions, such as troubleshooting or unjamming as well as planned cleaning and maintenance.
375c06b2-ee56-433c-bf56-1dac02d0e301.includes: Contact while cleaning, lubricating, unjamming, repairing, calibrating, testing, performing maintenance

f5006482-9221-46f8-81f9-351d39a9636f.title: Caught, entangled in running powered equipment— normal operation
f5006482-9221-46f8-81f9-351d39a9636f.definition: Contact with running machinery and equipment when a person, clothing, or part of body is pulled into moving parts of machinery or equipment.
f5006482-9221-46f8-81f9-351d39a9636f.includes: Clothing caught in running machinery and equipment in non-normal operation

f6740863-0cc2-456c-9c45-2b7a0187479a.title: Compressed between running equipment and other object(s)
f6740863-0cc2-456c-9c45-2b7a0187479a.definition: Struck or compressed between moving part of machine and another object or structure.
f6740863-0cc2-456c-9c45-2b7a0187479a.includes: Compressed between manlift platform and ceiling; compressed between machine arm and other object; pinned against wall by machine; caught in mechanical doors, gates, and windows
f6740863-0cc2-456c-9c45-2b7a0187479a.excludes: Pinned between vehicle body and attached vehicle part (665)

059aa8d2-82fa-4688-860e-4f59f87730f9.title: Struck by rolling powered vehicle or machinery
059aa8d2-82fa-4688-860e-4f59f87730f9.definition: Struck by a machine or vehicle moving over the ground surface that does not meet the definition of a transportation incident. That is, the machine is either not performing transportation functions (i.e. moving goods or persons) or is not in normal operation (i.e. moving outside of the control of a person or computer)
059aa8d2-82fa-4688-860e-4f59f87730f9.includes: Struck by moving machinery not involved in transport (e.g. robotic vacuum cleaner or inventory checker)

56cea215-f27d-44f5-b1b7-d99dfad6bdfe.title: Jarred, vibrated by running powered equipment
56cea215-f27d-44f5-b1b7-d99dfad6bdfe.definition: Cumulative trauma and injuries resulting from repeated or prolonged exposure to vibration or jarring.
56cea215-f27d-44f5-b1b7-d99dfad6bdfe.includes: Riding in jarring vehicle, without a specific transportation incident; acute injuries due to jarring and vibration of running machinery or nonpowered tools and objects
56cea215-f27d-44f5-b1b7-d99dfad6bdfe.excludes: vibration or jarring due to a transportation incident (2); abrasion due to short contact with powered equipment, such as belt sander (639)

2b5d7791-609f-4745-8432-23f74c039f92.title: Struck by running powered equipment— n.e.c.
2b5d7791-609f-4745-8432-23f74c039f92.definition: Struck by attached parts of running machinery and equipment.  Machine parts may be swinging, rotating, rising or lowering.
2b5d7791-609f-4745-8432-23f74c039f92.includes: Pushed by machine parts into another object, such as lifts compressing worker between lift platform and another object or surface; striking against part of powered equipment in operation
2b5d7791-609f-4745-8432-23f74c039f92.excludes: Struck by object or machine part detached from equipment (6422)

91d9bf66-d77b-4a23-a8f8-74a3abb68147.title: Contact with non-running objects or equipment
91d9bf66-d77b-4a23-a8f8-74a3abb68147.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of striking against or being struck by an object that is neither collapsing, falling, or propelled or operating under power. This group includes objects manipulated or wielded by the injured worker. Items or equipment being moved or wielded by other persons
91d9bf66-d77b-4a23-a8f8-74a3abb68147.includes: Walked into a wall, entangled in wire
91d9bf66-d77b-4a23-a8f8-74a3abb68147.excludes: Contact with running equipment and objects in normal or non-normal operation (65); falling objects or equipment (643); propelled, dislodged or discharged objects or substances (642); transportation incidents (Division 2)

801a81d0-775f-48b2-aa38-494ff1d3ef0d.title: Contact with non-running objects or equipment— unspecified
801a81d0-775f-48b2-aa38-494ff1d3ef0d.definition: Striking against or being struck by a non-running object that is not falling, moving over a surface or has not been discharged, dislodged or propelled when a more specific event code from 661 to 669 cannot be determined.

0ecdd780-9a5b-4061-a72c-7e1f7ca3f28b.title: Injured by object handled by person
0ecdd780-9a5b-4061-a72c-7e1f7ca3f28b.definition: Accidental contact resulting from a worker being struck by an object or equipment being handled or manipulated in some way by direct physical exertion of a person, either the injured worker themselves or another person.
0ecdd780-9a5b-4061-a72c-7e1f7ca3f28b.excludes: Powered tools or equipment whose operation does not involve direct physical exertion of a person (i.e. mechanically operated or remote-controlled machinery) (65)

24253f2f-6634-44e5-9b55-7b706e82fc76.title: Injured by object handled by person— unspecified

ce5ba544-6764-4746-a230-a0067c1af767.title: Injured by object held or wielded by person
ce5ba544-6764-4746-a230-a0067c1af767.definition: Accidental contact resulting from a worker being struck by an object or equipment being wielded or handled by themselves or another person

b36042ba-eaf9-44c6-87cc-f89811b1924a.title: Injured by object pushed or pulled by person
b36042ba-eaf9-44c6-87cc-f89811b1924a.definition: Accidental contact resulting from a worker being struck by an object or equipment being pushed or pulled by another person
b36042ba-eaf9-44c6-87cc-f89811b1924a.includes: Turning, steering object not supported by injured worker

cb8b57f8-9c35-474f-815e-16cefa2451d1.title: Injured by object handled by person— n.e.c.

47beaa88-638f-4260-8d54-c7877ac95418.title: Entangled in non-running object
47beaa88-638f-4260-8d54-c7877ac95418.definition: Objects that become wrapped around worker or part of body.
47beaa88-638f-4260-8d54-c7877ac95418.includes: Wrapped or surrounded by wire, rope, plastic
47beaa88-638f-4260-8d54-c7877ac95418.excludes: Caught or struck in collapsing structure (63)

3d3eadd1-544a-4f29-9c13-964738c7846c.title: Struck by rolling, sliding, or shifting objects—non-running
3d3eadd1-544a-4f29-9c13-964738c7846c.definition: Struck by rolling, sliding or shifting objects and equipment, except self-propelled, running powered equipment; items being pushed or pulled by person(s) or objects being advanced or propelled by powered equipment
3d3eadd1-544a-4f29-9c13-964738c7846c.includes: Rolling shopping cart, non running powered pallet jack sliding across a surface; struck by rolling logs or pipes; struck by object or equipment moving along fixed track (except transportation); struck by shifting stone slabs
3d3eadd1-544a-4f29-9c13-964738c7846c.excludes: Self-propelled, running powered equipment (653); items being pushed or pulled by person(s) (6622);  objects being advanced or propelled by powered equipment (659)

4bb7766a-2ae6-4563-b04d-a26a36219883.title: Caught or wedged between objects— nonrunning
4bb7766a-2ae6-4563-b04d-a26a36219883.definition: Impeded, caught, compressed or pinched in the parts of a single object or non-running equipment or between two objects or non-running equipment.

b434854a-06fc-49d6-9212-57c03374a7a6.title: Struck against stationary object
b434854a-06fc-49d6-9212-57c03374a7a6.definition: Codes in this group apply to injuries resulting from a person striking against an object where the impact is caused by the bodily motion of the injured person.
b434854a-06fc-49d6-9212-57c03374a7a6.excludes: intentionally striking or punching an object in anger or outburst (129)

f41eb9d1-c6bc-40ff-8899-9687b8ca429e.title: Struck against stationary object— unspecified
f41eb9d1-c6bc-40ff-8899-9687b8ca429e.definition: Injuries resulting from a person striking against an object where the impact is caused by the bodily motion of the injured person and a more detailed code from 6651 to 6659 cannot be determined

11b98274-523e-43bc-8de8-82f2421bab46.title: Stepped or knelt on object
11b98274-523e-43bc-8de8-82f2421bab46.definition: Making impact with an object by stepping on it, where the injury is from the impact not a loss of balance.

4a4983b1-e3ff-49fc-b408-c0e11ba2b643.title: Walked or ran into stationary object
4a4983b1-e3ff-49fc-b408-c0e11ba2b643.definition: Injuries from inadvertently walking into an object or structure.

d69c5bf6-e22c-412d-a744-95390a6d8269.title: Struck against stationary object while rising, lowering
d69c5bf6-e22c-412d-a744-95390a6d8269.definition: Injuries resulting from a person striking against an object where the impact is caused by the bodily motion of the injured person rising up from a crouched or seated position
d69c5bf6-e22c-412d-a744-95390a6d8269.includes: Strike head while crawling, crouching under something

dc471ef2-b51f-423f-8f8a-8cfee37a0f86.title: Struck against stationary object— n.e.c.
dc471ef2-b51f-423f-8f8a-8cfee37a0f86.definition: Injuries resulting from a person striking against an object where the impact is caused by the bodily motion of the injured person that do not meet descriptions of 6651 through 6653
dc471ef2-b51f-423f-8f8a-8cfee37a0f86.includes: Splinters from non-handheld objects (e.g. railing); jarring injuries from repeated striking of non-powered tools, such as a hammer or axe
dc471ef2-b51f-423f-8f8a-8cfee37a0f86.excludes: Contact with moving or running parts (65)

fb3467fc-b619-4e4f-83e1-e37d96c1c0c7.title: Rubbed or abraded by non-running object
fb3467fc-b619-4e4f-83e1-e37d96c1c0c7.definition: Injuries or discomfort resulting from acute or prolonged exposure to friction or pressure.
fb3467fc-b619-4e4f-83e1-e37d96c1c0c7.includes: Blisters and chafing from worn apparel

4be7c495-ef81-4f85-8aa4-9f1fdff68ae0.title: Other contact with non-running objects or equipment— n.e.c.
4be7c495-ef81-4f85-8aa4-9f1fdff68ae0.definition: Contact with non-running objects or equipment that is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 661 or 666.
4be7c495-ef81-4f85-8aa4-9f1fdff68ae0.excludes: jarred or jerked by non-powered object

cad8726a-a8ab-4851-a9c1-cab2689cb47c.title: OVEREXERTION, REPETITIVE MOTION, AND BODILY CONDITIONS
cad8726a-a8ab-4851-a9c1-cab2689cb47c.definition: Codes in this division apply to injuries that are the result of either excessive physical effort over an outside source, free bodily motion, the assumption of an unnatural position, repetition of a bodily motion, maintaining one position for an extended period, or a combination of any of these.
cad8726a-a8ab-4851-a9c1-cab2689cb47c.includes: Heart attacks and strokes not attributed to a specific event or exposure; "Ergonomic injuries"
cad8726a-a8ab-4851-a9c1-cab2689cb47c.excludes: Overexertion injuries occurring onboard vehicles in transport (Division 2); abnormal stepping, loss of balance, trips, slips or falls and injuries from attempting to recover from these events (Division 4)

06527bc9-a750-4117-824a-f33f3311ccbf.title: Overexertion, repetitive motion and bodily condition— unspecified
06527bc9-a750-4117-824a-f33f3311ccbf.definition: Overexertion or ergonomic Injury not stated to be caused by violence, transportation, fire or explosion, fall, exposure, or contact, and a more specific code from 710 through 799 cannot be determined.
06527bc9-a750-4117-824a-f33f3311ccbf.includes: Overexertion or ergonomic injury from normal or regular duties; working at work station; strain due to installation; scrubbing, cleaning, dusting, etc. without additional information

e661c7de-683e-4233-b0cd-238bee6b9788.title: Overexertion while moving or manipulating external object(s)
e661c7de-683e-4233-b0cd-238bee6b9788.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries that are the result of excessive physical effort directed at an outside source, either as a single or cumulative exposure.
e661c7de-683e-4233-b0cd-238bee6b9788.includes: Lifting/lowering, pulling/pushing/turning, moving/transferring, holding/carrying/wielding, or catching/throwing an object or person
e661c7de-683e-4233-b0cd-238bee6b9788.excludes: Non-overexertion injuries from contact with a person (61)

dca2a1b3-c74e-4b6b-ad53-5cb51cc0ccbe.title: Overexertion while moving or manipulating external object(s)— unspecified
dca2a1b3-c74e-4b6b-ad53-5cb51cc0ccbe.definition: Overexertions involving an outside source for an unspecified length of time and unspecified number of repetitions when the type of exertion reflected in codes 711 through 719 cannot be determined.
dca2a1b3-c74e-4b6b-ad53-5cb51cc0ccbe.includes: "Moving" an object without further information; unspecified overexertion involving an object or person such as cleaning or making a bed

71d7cc91-439a-46ac-b88e-529e781ae695.title: Overexertion while providing medical or custodial care
71d7cc91-439a-46ac-b88e-529e781ae695.definition: Overexertion incurred while attempting to move or physically assist a person when the worker bears part or all of another person's weight or exerts against another person's strength.
71d7cc91-439a-46ac-b88e-529e781ae695.includes: Transferring, repositioning, or turning  a patient; overexertion from assisting or helping a patient/person without further information; catching a falling patient or child; Pushing or pulling a patient in a wheelchair, bed, or stretcher
71d7cc91-439a-46ac-b88e-529e781ae695.excludes: overexertion when restraining a violent person (Division 1); veterinary care (711); pushing or pulling a bed, wheelchair or stretcher without a patient or if it is unknown if there was a patient (714)

06ee1140-7897-4ca3-b5c8-77233e53a15b.title: Overexertion while wielding, manipulating tools, object(s)
06ee1140-7897-4ca3-b5c8-77233e53a15b.definition: Overexertions from combinations of gross motor movements and exertions while wielding handtools or manipulating other objects.
06ee1140-7897-4ca3-b5c8-77233e53a15b.includes: Shoveling; cranking; hammering; single instance use of handheld tools/objects, such as shoveling;  interacting with levers or switches; turning a crank handle; manually jacking up a vehicle; turning or rotating objects without relocating them; opening doors or windows; tightening

35629630-70dc-418d-a6fe-fa9f6c07ab55.title: Overexertion while catching or throwing object(s)
35629630-70dc-418d-a6fe-fa9f6c07ab55.definition: Overexertion from throwing or catching an object or person, either once or repeatedly, when injury is not caused by impact with the thrown object.

b9a559ed-cbd9-420d-ba15-06586b7aa44e.title: Overexertion while materials moving by hand
b9a559ed-cbd9-420d-ba15-06586b7aa44e.definition: Overexertions from bearing the weight of or striving against the resistance of an object while trying to relocate or position it. The overexertion may be a single episode or the result of prolonged or multiple instances of exertion. This includes lifting, lowering, pushing, pulling, turning, and other manners of exertion.
b9a559ed-cbd9-420d-ba15-06586b7aa44e.includes: Lifting, lowering, carrying, supporting, handling, holding, or placing an object;  stocking merchandise; team lifting large objects; pushing, pulling or turning objects or equipment over ground surface, with or without wheels; moving objects up or down stairs; moving furniture; unloading freight; Pushing or pulling a wheelchair, bed, or stretcher that was empty or if it was unknown whether there was a patient.

e330efd4-283e-4c6b-894f-d30bfec6f910.title: Multiple types of overexertion while moving or manipulating external object(s)
e330efd4-283e-4c6b-894f-d30bfec6f910.definition: Combination of overexertions from at least 2 different codes 711 through 714, occurring either once or multiple times.
e330efd4-283e-4c6b-894f-d30bfec6f910.includes: Overexertion catching a dropped object and then moving it

019eb862-67ba-4403-9394-21f54ebb7fb3.title: Overexertion while moving or manipulating external object(s)— n.e.c.
019eb862-67ba-4403-9394-21f54ebb7fb3.definition: Overexertion for which the event is known but does not fit descriptions of event codes 710 to 718.
019eb862-67ba-4403-9394-21f54ebb7fb3.includes: Kicking a ball; attempting to stop a rolling object; overexertion or ergonomic injury from worn apparel or items (e.g. backpacks, utility belts); overexertion while working with animals, animal husbandry, veterinary care
019eb862-67ba-4403-9394-21f54ebb7fb3.excludes: Bearing down on shovel with foot (712)

accb34ef-172e-45bd-a13e-9f776328c631.title: Repetitive microtasks
accb34ef-172e-45bd-a13e-9f776328c631.definition: Codes in this major group apply injuries or conditions resulting from motions (often micro tasks) that impose stress or strain on some part of the body due to the repetitive nature of the task.
accb34ef-172e-45bd-a13e-9f776328c631.excludes: Strenuous effort or exertion imposed against an outside source (71); repetitive (cumulative trauma), vibration

b760f425-763f-4b10-8e06-79b6baa2c89f.title: Repetitive microtasks— unspecified
b760f425-763f-4b10-8e06-79b6baa2c89f.definition: Repetitive motion without overexertion that does not have enough information to choose a more specific event code from 721 through 729.

dda4e42d-719f-4349-8739-d84bec7e8806.title: Repetitive microtasks involving computers, electronics
dda4e42d-719f-4349-8739-d84bec7e8806.definition: Repetitive motion involving data entry tools or equipment
dda4e42d-719f-4349-8739-d84bec7e8806.includes: Repeated use of computer peripherals, cash registers, or cellular phones; gaming equipment; touch screens

8b5b1326-f19d-447b-9699-907a5e79d223.title: Repetitive use of tools, instruments
8b5b1326-f19d-447b-9699-907a5e79d223.definition: Repetitive motion involving the use of simple tools or equipment without overexertion.
8b5b1326-f19d-447b-9699-907a5e79d223.includes: Repeated use of screwdrivers, knives, musical instruments, or surgical implements; musical instruments; product assembly
8b5b1326-f19d-447b-9699-907a5e79d223.excludes: Holding or wielding a heavy tool (712)

0ec61822-faf7-41a2-abad-d0f945d566d6.title: Multiple types of repetitive microtasks
0ec61822-faf7-41a2-abad-d0f945d566d6.definition: Combination of at least 2 different repetitive motions from codes 721 through 722.
0ec61822-faf7-41a2-abad-d0f945d566d6.includes: Trigger finger caused by a combination of texting and using handheld tools

8a3194cc-3814-45a6-b05d-b827e6329de9.title: Repetitive microtasks— n.e.c.
8a3194cc-3814-45a6-b05d-b827e6329de9.definition: Specific repetitive motion, not involving tools and/or instruments that is known but does not fit the description of event codes from 721 through 728.
8a3194cc-3814-45a6-b05d-b827e6329de9.includes: Sign language interpretation, scanning groceries, assembly-line work without tools; stepping on pedal repeatedly; voice strain after prolonged talking/shouting

e4ab9b8c-4aa8-4794-b7ca-4559931165ad.title: Bodily position and motion
e4ab9b8c-4aa8-4794-b7ca-4559931165ad.definition: Codes in this major group apply to injuries or conditions resulting from a single or prolonged instance(s) of free bodily motion or the assumption of a physical position without other incident, which impose stress or strain upon some part of the body.
e4ab9b8c-4aa8-4794-b7ca-4559931165ad.includes: prolonged sitting, standing, or viewing; musculoskeletal or other injury or illnesses resulting from the execution of personal movements such as walking, climbing, or bending when such movement in itself was the source of injury or illness; eyestrain from sustained viewing (737)
e4ab9b8c-4aa8-4794-b7ca-4559931165ad.excludes: overexertion from lifting, pulling, or pushing outside objects  (71); motions involving microtasks which induce injury or illness due to their repetitive nature (72); abnormal stepping, loss of balance, trips, slips and falls, which are coded in (4); injuries from attempting to catch oneself while falling or recover balance after slipping or tripping (4)

46043ac8-e308-4586-8a36-a4df70c64271.title: Bodily position and motion— unspecified
46043ac8-e308-4586-8a36-a4df70c64271.definition: Bodily motion, either a single episode or prolonged, when the specific action is unknown and a more specific event code from 731 through 739 cannot be determined.
46043ac8-e308-4586-8a36-a4df70c64271.includes: Body parts "giving out" with no explanation or external source

ccc959d0-4326-48dd-add1-fdf22722455c.title: Climbing or stepping— up or down
ccc959d0-4326-48dd-add1-fdf22722455c.definition: Overexertion from raising or lowering self from one surface to another without stumble, loss or balance or other incident. This can be a single episode or prolonged.
ccc959d0-4326-48dd-add1-fdf22722455c.includes: Strained back when ascending or descending stairs, ladders, or inclines; overexertion while boarding and alighting vehicles; "hoisting" oneself to a higher level or surface
ccc959d0-4326-48dd-add1-fdf22722455c.excludes: Stepping on a flat surface (736); slip, trip, stumble while stepping, loss of balance, fall (43); "missed step" (42); twisting ankle due to stepping on uneven surface (432)

98ecc564-3a13-4653-8105-0da66f52a9e1.title: Kneeling, crawling
98ecc564-3a13-4653-8105-0da66f52a9e1.definition: Bodily movement involving a single or prolonged episode of body weight being placed on knees through kneeling or crawling. It also includes assuming a kneeling position and changing from a kneeling position to another position.

83d03981-64ba-4650-b259-25854fdf086f.title: Twisting, reaching, bending
83d03981-64ba-4650-b259-25854fdf086f.definition: Bodily movement involving a single or prolonged episode of twisting, extending, or contorting oneself in attempts to reach items or fit into spaces.
83d03981-64ba-4650-b259-25854fdf086f.includes: Straining for out of reach items

295e594d-82f5-49dd-a06c-4a4a6c911182.title: Standing up, sitting down, laying down
295e594d-82f5-49dd-a06c-4a4a6c911182.definition: Bodily movement involving a single or prolonged episode of sustained stance or position or repeated transition between standing, sitting or laying.
295e594d-82f5-49dd-a06c-4a4a6c911182.includes: Laying down under a vehicle to perform repair work

a1e7b1e8-24a1-4604-b80e-d3f200a1b5f4.title: Running, without other incident
a1e7b1e8-24a1-4604-b80e-d3f200a1b5f4.definition: Running without loss of balance, abnormal step, or stepping on an object or uneven surface.
a1e7b1e8-24a1-4604-b80e-d3f200a1b5f4.includes: Single episode of running to pursue suspect
a1e7b1e8-24a1-4604-b80e-d3f200a1b5f4.excludes: running during athletic training or competition

8ab1fe16-6b66-456a-aea2-b4268e229e5d.title: Walking, without other incident
8ab1fe16-6b66-456a-aea2-b4268e229e5d.definition: Walking without loss of balance, abnormal step, or stepping on an object or uneven surface.

4950a4cf-9d67-4d72-95f5-4a868bfea549.title: Sustained bodily position
4950a4cf-9d67-4d72-95f5-4a868bfea549.definition: Holding a natural position for any length of time that does not fit the description of event codes 731 through 734.
4950a4cf-9d67-4d72-95f5-4a868bfea549.includes: Poor workstation ergonomics, including seats on vehicles in transport in the absence of a transportation incident; prolonged or brief episodes of sitting, standing or squatting; sustained viewing of screens or monitors; operating a vehicle without transportation incident or rough driving surface
4950a4cf-9d67-4d72-95f5-4a868bfea549.excludes: Welder's flash, staring at the sun (522)

9ffb9d6b-adb3-47de-8c0a-cadb13112159.title: Multiple types of bodily position and motion
9ffb9d6b-adb3-47de-8c0a-cadb13112159.definition: Combination of at least two bodily reactions from codes 731 through 737 without loss of balance, abnormal step, or stepping on an object.
9ffb9d6b-adb3-47de-8c0a-cadb13112159.includes: Single or repeated episodes of standing and walking, walking and running, or kneeling and standing,

a0584b04-63c0-4a13-9648-92eed88b0ab3.title: Bodily position and motion—  n.e.c.
a0584b04-63c0-4a13-9648-92eed88b0ab3.definition: Bodily motion that is known but does not fit the description of event codes from 731 through 738.

366d4487-a9c6-4308-959b-c0813b59a475.title: Bodily conditions
366d4487-a9c6-4308-959b-c0813b59a475.definition: Injuries or illnesses that are the direct result of the physical condition of the worker with no outside injury component.
366d4487-a9c6-4308-959b-c0813b59a475.includes: Heart attacks and strokes which are not attributed to a specific event or exposure; unexplained fainting; vertigo, motion sickness if not related to transportation
366d4487-a9c6-4308-959b-c0813b59a475.excludes: Bodily conditions exacerbated by workplace events or exposures (code to appropriate event); anxiety or other mental symptoms or disorders due to violent incidents (11), witnessing a violent act (13), transportation incidents (Division 2) or stressful environments (57)

cc98f2ce-c59f-40c5-a87e-de04e171690f.title: Multiple types of overexertions, bodily motion and position
cc98f2ce-c59f-40c5-a87e-de04e171690f.definition: Combination of at least two separate, sequential events from the overexertion involving external objects (71), repetitive microtasks (72), bodily position and motion (73) and bodily conditions (74) during a single or prolonged episode.
cc98f2ce-c59f-40c5-a87e-de04e171690f.includes: Assembly line work involving exertion of strength and repetitive microtasks

83e6344f-06d4-43b7-a7f4-e8ae31286f0d.title: Event or exposure— unspecified
83e6344f-06d4-43b7-a7f4-e8ae31286f0d.definition: Select this code when there is not enough information present to select a code from any of the major event divisions (1-7).
